WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.630
Alif Laam, Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum

00:00:10.630 --> 00:00:18.230
Nazala alayka Al-Kitab Bil-Haqq Musabdiqal Lima Bayna Yadihi Wa Anzala Al-Tawrat Wa Al-Injeel

00:00:18.230 --> 00:00:22.230
Min Qablu Hudal Lill-Nas Wa Anzala Al-Furqan

00:00:22.230 --> 00:00:27.630
Inna Allatheena Kafaru Bi Ayatillahi Lahum Adhabu Shadeed

00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:31.430
Wa Allahu Azizun Unthu Intiqam

00:00:31.430 --> 00:00:36.430
Inna Allaha La Yakhda Alayhi Shajajin Fi Al-Ardi Wa La Fi Al-Sama

00:00:36.430 --> 00:00:39.430
Bismillahir Rahmanir Raheem, Alhamdulillahi Rabbil Alameen

00:00:39.430 --> 00:00:42.330
Wa Salatu Wa Salamul Atamanil Akmalani

00:00:42.330 --> 00:00:45.430
Ala Khayri Khalqihi Ajma'ina Wa Ba'a

00:00:45.430 --> 00:00:52.930
All praises due to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, complete blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:00:52.930 --> 00:00:59.430
his wives, his entire household, all his companions, may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them all

00:00:59.430 --> 00:01:03.430
and may Allah bless every single one of us and grant us all goodness.

00:01:03.430 --> 00:01:12.930
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam, we are fortunate that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has given us the opportunity to listen to this Quran in the month of Ramadan,

00:01:12.930 --> 00:01:19.430
to read the Quran and to be able to understand the message of the Quran to a certain extent

00:01:19.430 --> 00:01:24.930
and to be able to expand the knowledge that we have of the Quran in this month of the Quran.

00:01:24.930 --> 00:01:33.430
So take that as a gift of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala and do not lose the opportunity to listen to the pure reading of the Quran

00:01:33.430 --> 00:01:36.930
and to learn, to put into practice and to convey to others.

00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:41.930
Yesterday we were looking at the birth, the most blessed birth that ever occurred

00:01:41.930 --> 00:01:45.430
and that was the birth of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:01:45.430 --> 00:01:51.430
the best of creation, the one whom Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala chose for us to be from his Ummah.

00:01:51.430 --> 00:02:01.430
So indeed, we are very very fortunate and as we say, it's about time we knew a little bit more about his life sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:02:01.430 --> 00:02:06.430
The place that was chosen for this birth was Makkatul Mukarramah.

00:02:06.430 --> 00:02:11.430
It is the center of the earth. If you take a look at where it is, it is the center of the earth.

00:02:11.430 --> 00:02:20.930
And there is the Kaaba that was built right at the beginning by Ibrahim a.s.w. together with Ismail a.s.w.

00:02:20.930 --> 00:02:25.930
And throughout history it was rebuilt as and when the floods came in

00:02:25.930 --> 00:02:32.930
and sometimes destruction was caused by fires and so on and it was rebuilt but exactly on the same spot.

00:02:32.930 --> 00:02:36.930
We heard about the well of Zamzam yesterday, a very interesting story.

00:02:36.930 --> 00:02:39.930
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to grant us goodness.

00:02:39.930 --> 00:02:46.930
Very important to note that the person who saw Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam first,

00:02:46.930 --> 00:02:54.930
it is reported that a person known as Ash-Shifa, Ummu Abdur Rahman ibn Awf,

00:02:54.930 --> 00:02:59.930
the mother of Abdur Rahman ibn Awf, one of the narrations say that she was the midwife.

00:02:59.930 --> 00:03:06.930
So obviously the midwife is the first one who takes the child and this is the great fortune of this particular lady,

00:03:06.930 --> 00:03:13.930
the mother of Abdur Rahman ibn Awf who later on became one of the wealthiest of the Sahaba, that particular man.

00:03:13.930 --> 00:03:18.930
Also what is of importance is Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam when he was born,

00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:21.930
he did not have a father as we said yesterday.

00:03:21.930 --> 00:03:26.930
His father had passed away already when he was seven months in the womb of his mother.

00:03:26.930 --> 00:03:33.930
And from this we need to realize that Allah chose for the best of creation to be an orphan.

00:03:33.930 --> 00:03:39.930
So no one who is an orphan here should think for a moment that that is a negative point.

00:03:39.930 --> 00:03:41.930
It is one of the most positive points.

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:47.930
When a person does not have a father, Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala replaces that with so many other virtues,

00:03:47.930 --> 00:03:53.930
so many other things, so many other people who take care and sometimes they may have a difficult upbringing

00:03:53.930 --> 00:03:58.930
but Allah presents for them opportunities that he has not presented for others.

00:03:58.930 --> 00:04:03.930
Look at this, the greatest leader of all, he was an orphan.

00:04:03.930 --> 00:04:09.930
And not only that, in Islam the meaning of the term orphan is the child who does not have a father,

00:04:09.930 --> 00:04:12.930
who lost his or her father, that is the orphan.

00:04:12.930 --> 00:04:19.930
If someone has lost a mother, they are not termed as yateem in the Arabic language on condition that they still have the father.

00:04:19.930 --> 00:04:22.930
But the minute they've lost the father, then they are considered yateem.

00:04:22.930 --> 00:04:28.930
This is the Islamic interpretation of it, although from an English language perspective it is a little bit different.

00:04:28.930 --> 00:04:34.930
So Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam's father passed away when he was 25 years old,

00:04:34.930 --> 00:04:37.930
meaning the man himself Abdullah ibn Abdul Muttalib.

00:04:37.930 --> 00:04:44.930
And as for what happened to him when he was born, his grandfather loved him so much because Abdul Muttalib,

00:04:44.930 --> 00:04:49.930
who was the grandfather of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam, had already had information,

00:04:49.930 --> 00:04:55.930
as we said yesterday from various parties telling him you are going to be the grandfather of a child

00:04:55.930 --> 00:04:58.930
who is going to really be a leader and so on.

00:04:58.930 --> 00:05:03.930
So he took great care and he was very interested in this daughter-in-law,

00:05:03.930 --> 00:05:12.930
or should I say the little grandchild that was born and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala placed in his heart love of this particular child,

00:05:12.930 --> 00:05:18.930
although he was meant to die just a little while later.

00:05:18.930 --> 00:05:23.930
So if we take a look, it's easy for us to say the mother looked after the child,

00:05:23.930 --> 00:05:29.930
but the man who was behind the scenes was Abdul Muttalib, he was there.

00:05:29.930 --> 00:05:36.930
And the mother looked after Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam together with her slave girl,

00:05:36.930 --> 00:05:39.930
very important for us to know who was the slave girl.

00:05:39.930 --> 00:05:41.930
Her name was Ummu Ayman.

00:05:41.930 --> 00:05:43.930
Ummu Ayman Baraka binti Ta'alaba.

00:05:43.930 --> 00:05:46.930
That was her name later to be known as Radhiallahu anha.

00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:52.930
She was a slave girl from Africa and she was the slave of Amina binti Wahab.

00:05:52.930 --> 00:05:54.930
Subhanallah.

00:05:54.930 --> 00:05:56.930
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:05:56.930 --> 00:05:59.930
after my mother, I consider her a mother.

00:05:59.930 --> 00:06:00.930
Allahu Akbar.

00:06:00.930 --> 00:06:02.930
After my mother, I consider her a mother.

00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:04.930
Ummu Ayman Radhiallahu anha.

00:06:04.930 --> 00:06:07.930
She looked after the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:06:07.930 --> 00:06:11.930
Some narrations make mention of how she was a witness.

00:06:11.930 --> 00:06:14.930
She also nursed Nabi sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:06:14.930 --> 00:06:18.930
prior to him going to the clan of Banu Sa'ad

00:06:18.930 --> 00:06:23.930
where he was nursed by Halimatu Sa'diyyah.

00:06:23.930 --> 00:06:26.930
If we take a look at this, it is a great virtue.

00:06:26.930 --> 00:06:31.930
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam being looked after by so many people.

00:06:31.930 --> 00:06:34.930
And as he grew up, in fact, in his infancy,

00:06:34.930 --> 00:06:39.930
there was a habit amongst the people of Mecca at the time,

00:06:39.930 --> 00:06:42.930
Quraysh and the Arab clans and tribes that lived in the cities.

00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:46.930
In the cities, people swear, they shout, they scream.

00:06:46.930 --> 00:06:48.930
Perhaps the air is not that clean.

00:06:48.930 --> 00:06:55.930
So they used to send their children to pure environment in the Bedouin villages.

00:06:55.930 --> 00:06:59.930
And there was a village known as Badiyah to Banu Sa'ad.

00:06:59.930 --> 00:07:00.930
Banu Sa'ad used to live there.

00:07:00.930 --> 00:07:04.930
It was one of the top villages where people used to send their infants

00:07:04.930 --> 00:07:07.930
to be breastfed with the pure milk.

00:07:07.930 --> 00:07:10.930
And when we say pure milk, non-contaminated.

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.930
Today, subhanallah, we have a different type of contamination.

00:07:14.930 --> 00:07:17.930
And that is the genetically modified food that we have.

00:07:17.930 --> 00:07:20.930
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us from food that is bad for us.

00:07:20.930 --> 00:07:24.930
Sometimes we don't even know what is the content of what we are eating.

00:07:24.930 --> 00:07:28.930
And we don't realize it is sometimes not fit for animal consumption.

00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:30.930
Forget about human beings.

00:07:30.930 --> 00:07:31.930
And still we're busy eating it.

00:07:31.930 --> 00:07:34.930
And as they say in our language, just chow man.

00:07:34.930 --> 00:07:35.930
Allahu Akbar.

00:07:35.930 --> 00:07:38.930
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a deep understanding.

00:07:38.930 --> 00:07:42.930
Food, it's up to us to make sure we are eating that which is halal

00:07:42.930 --> 00:07:44.930
and that which is healthy.

00:07:44.930 --> 00:07:47.930
So they used to send their children out to learn good language.

00:07:47.930 --> 00:07:49.930
The language was powerful.

00:07:49.930 --> 00:07:51.930
The manners, the mannerisms, the etiquettes.

00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:54.930
And Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam, he was a little orphan.

00:07:54.930 --> 00:07:57.930
They were waiting for the people to come from Banu Sa'ad

00:07:57.930 --> 00:07:59.930
and from various other villages.

00:07:59.930 --> 00:08:01.930
So when the people of Banu Sa'ad came,

00:08:01.930 --> 00:08:03.930
there is a very, very interesting story.

00:08:03.930 --> 00:08:06.930
Khadija binti, sorry, Haleematu al-Sa'diya,

00:08:06.930 --> 00:08:10.930
who was ultimately taking Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:08:10.930 --> 00:08:11.930
took him actually.

00:08:11.930 --> 00:08:14.930
Initially when she was coming to Mecca al-Mukarramah,

00:08:14.930 --> 00:08:16.930
she was riding with the rest of her colleagues

00:08:16.930 --> 00:08:20.930
who were also going out to look for people whom they could look after

00:08:20.930 --> 00:08:24.930
in their particular village from Quraysh.

00:08:24.930 --> 00:08:26.930
And with that because they were poor,

00:08:26.930 --> 00:08:29.930
they felt we would probably get a little bit of wealth from it.

00:08:29.930 --> 00:08:31.930
And perhaps people might give us something.

00:08:31.930 --> 00:08:32.930
And we might earn a little bit.

00:08:32.930 --> 00:08:34.930
And we can even look after these children

00:08:34.930 --> 00:08:36.930
and send them back to their folks after some time.

00:08:36.930 --> 00:08:39.930
So Khadija, sorry, Haleematu al-Sa'diya,

00:08:39.930 --> 00:08:41.930
she makes mention of something very interesting.

00:08:41.930 --> 00:08:45.930
She says the donkey I was on got injured on its knee.

00:08:45.930 --> 00:08:47.930
And it began to bleed.

00:08:47.930 --> 00:08:48.930
And it was slow.

00:08:48.930 --> 00:08:49.930
And it slowed down.

00:08:49.930 --> 00:08:52.930
So myself and my husband, we arrived in Mecca

00:08:52.930 --> 00:08:54.930
after the rest of them had arrived.

00:08:54.930 --> 00:08:57.930
And they had already selected the babies they wanted to take.

00:08:57.930 --> 00:08:59.930
The baby of the rich man, the baby of this man,

00:08:59.930 --> 00:09:01.930
baby of this man, baby of that person,

00:09:01.930 --> 00:09:03.930
baby of this elite and this elite.

00:09:03.930 --> 00:09:05.930
And when she came, there was one child remaining.

00:09:05.930 --> 00:09:06.930
Who was that?

00:09:06.930 --> 00:09:09.930
This was the plan of Allah for the donkey to be delayed.

00:09:09.930 --> 00:09:11.930
This is why we tell everyone,

00:09:11.930 --> 00:09:13.930
when you are delayed, don't worry, Allah has a plan.

00:09:13.930 --> 00:09:15.930
He knows why this has happened.

00:09:15.930 --> 00:09:16.930
Just say Alhamdulillah.

00:09:16.930 --> 00:09:19.930
Like they say, better late than never.

00:09:19.930 --> 00:09:22.930
And in some cases they say, better late than the late.

00:09:22.930 --> 00:09:23.930
Allahu Akbar.

00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:25.930
May Allah have mercy on some who have passed away.

00:09:25.930 --> 00:09:28.930
I heard this morning that there were some youngsters

00:09:28.930 --> 00:09:30.930
who had passed away in KwaZulu Natal.

00:09:30.930 --> 00:09:32.930
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant them Jannah.

00:09:32.930 --> 00:09:36.930
They were granted a death in this particular month of Ramadan.

00:09:36.930 --> 00:09:39.930
And we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to be pleased with them,

00:09:39.930 --> 00:09:42.930
to forgive their shortcomings and to be pleased with all of us

00:09:42.930 --> 00:09:44.930
and to also grant us a blessed death.

00:09:44.930 --> 00:09:45.930
So she was delayed.

00:09:45.930 --> 00:09:47.930
When she came, she saw this orphan child.

00:09:47.930 --> 00:09:49.930
Now, no one wants to take an orphan child

00:09:49.930 --> 00:09:51.930
because there's no father figure here.

00:09:51.930 --> 00:09:52.930
Who is going to pay?

00:09:52.930 --> 00:09:55.930
Who is going to, you know, be responsible and so on?

00:09:55.930 --> 00:09:57.930
So she thought, let me quickly have a peep

00:09:57.930 --> 00:09:58.930
or someone else.

00:09:58.930 --> 00:10:01.930
If not, then she did not want to go back to her village

00:10:01.930 --> 00:10:02.930
without anyone.

00:10:02.930 --> 00:10:04.930
So instead of facing the others,

00:10:04.930 --> 00:10:06.930
saying, you went all the way to Quraysh,

00:10:06.930 --> 00:10:08.930
you came back without a child.

00:10:08.930 --> 00:10:10.930
She then decided afterwards that,

00:10:10.930 --> 00:10:12.930
okay, let me take this orphan child.

00:10:12.930 --> 00:10:13.930
Allahu Akbar.

00:10:13.930 --> 00:10:15.930
She makes mention later on.

00:10:15.930 --> 00:10:18.930
And she says, we took the child

00:10:18.930 --> 00:10:20.930
and immediately we started feeling blessings.

00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:22.930
Jumped onto the donkey

00:10:22.930 --> 00:10:24.930
and suddenly the donkey became strong.

00:10:24.930 --> 00:10:26.930
And the wound of the donkey healed.

00:10:26.930 --> 00:10:27.930
Allahu Akbar.

00:10:27.930 --> 00:10:29.930
Weren't we talking about miracles?

00:10:29.930 --> 00:10:31.930
The wound of the donkey healed.

00:10:31.930 --> 00:10:34.930
And suddenly it was one of the stronger donkeys

00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:36.930
and it was leading the pack.

00:10:36.930 --> 00:10:38.930
And we arrived in Banu Sa'ad.

00:10:38.930 --> 00:10:39.930
And to our amazement,

00:10:39.930 --> 00:10:42.930
we found that the goats and the sheep that were there,

00:10:42.930 --> 00:10:45.930
the milk within the udders was already so much

00:10:45.930 --> 00:10:47.930
and we could never drink so much before.

00:10:47.930 --> 00:10:49.930
And now there was a surplus of milk.

00:10:49.930 --> 00:10:52.930
Subhanallah, something had happened.

00:10:52.930 --> 00:10:55.930
We found, strangely, it began to rain also.

00:10:55.930 --> 00:10:57.930
And what happened is, the flowers came out.

00:10:57.930 --> 00:10:59.930
They began to blossom.

00:10:59.930 --> 00:11:01.930
And the shrubberies and the little bushes

00:11:01.930 --> 00:11:03.930
and so on began to come out.

00:11:03.930 --> 00:11:05.930
A little bit of the greenery and so on.

00:11:05.930 --> 00:11:06.930
And we were amazed.

00:11:06.930 --> 00:11:08.930
And there was so much blessing.

00:11:08.930 --> 00:11:12.930
She says, my breast milk was not enough for the one child.

00:11:12.930 --> 00:11:13.930
And now there was so much

00:11:13.930 --> 00:11:15.930
that that child also stopped crying

00:11:15.930 --> 00:11:17.930
and this child also fed.

00:11:17.930 --> 00:11:18.930
And this child was so amazing,

00:11:18.930 --> 00:11:20.930
sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:22.930
that whenever he wanted to sleep,

00:11:22.930 --> 00:11:24.930
he would look up into the skies

00:11:24.930 --> 00:11:25.930
and then he would go to sleep.

00:11:25.930 --> 00:11:28.930
And whenever I removed his clothes to bathe him,

00:11:28.930 --> 00:11:31.930
he would cry until I clothed him once again.

00:11:31.930 --> 00:11:34.930
Subhanallah, sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:11:34.930 --> 00:11:39.300
And so many beautiful points she makes mention of.

00:11:39.300 --> 00:11:43.300
She actually speaks of how the house was full of blessing

00:11:43.300 --> 00:11:47.300
and how the entire badiyah,

00:11:47.300 --> 00:11:49.300
the entire group of villages that was there,

00:11:49.300 --> 00:11:50.300
was full of blessing.

00:11:50.300 --> 00:11:55.300
And he was not a child who used to be like the ordinary children

00:11:55.300 --> 00:11:56.300
fighting over small things.

00:11:56.300 --> 00:11:58.300
He was very calm and relaxed.

00:11:58.300 --> 00:12:01.300
And he grew up with the eloquence,

00:12:01.300 --> 00:12:03.300
speaking powerful language

00:12:03.300 --> 00:12:06.300
from the very, very early ages of his life.

00:12:06.300 --> 00:12:07.300
Powerful language.

00:12:07.300 --> 00:12:10.300
As I told you, Banu Sa'd were like the best.

00:12:10.300 --> 00:12:12.300
They were the most sought after

00:12:12.300 --> 00:12:14.300
for people to take the children away.

00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:17.300
You know, there is a point I raised today

00:12:17.300 --> 00:12:19.300
earlier on when I had a little radio program.

00:12:19.300 --> 00:12:22.300
That look at how the kuffar of Quraysh

00:12:22.300 --> 00:12:25.300
used to send their children away for benefit.

00:12:25.300 --> 00:12:29.300
We sometimes feel so clingy upon our children

00:12:29.300 --> 00:12:32.300
that we cannot send them in order to be a hafil

00:12:32.300 --> 00:12:33.300
for a year or two.

00:12:33.300 --> 00:12:35.300
And these people were ready to send them for dunya.

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:38.300
And they were ready to send them for morals and character.

00:12:38.300 --> 00:12:40.300
We can't even part with our children sometimes.

00:12:40.300 --> 00:12:43.300
And we haven't even inculcated in our children

00:12:43.300 --> 00:12:45.300
how important it is sometimes

00:12:45.300 --> 00:12:47.300
to actually be separated from the parents

00:12:47.300 --> 00:12:49.300
in order for them to prepare for a day

00:12:49.300 --> 00:12:51.300
when they won't have those parents.

00:12:51.300 --> 00:12:53.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:12:53.300 --> 00:12:55.300
and grant us foresightedness.

00:12:55.300 --> 00:12:57.300
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect our children

00:12:57.300 --> 00:13:00.300
and make us parents who are always exemplary

00:13:00.300 --> 00:13:02.300
making the right decisions.

00:13:02.300 --> 00:13:04.300
So here, the Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:04.300 --> 00:13:08.300
being in this particular badiyah with these children

00:13:08.300 --> 00:13:11.300
as he grew up, something happened.

00:13:11.300 --> 00:13:12.300
What happened?

00:13:12.300 --> 00:13:14.300
They used to play outside with the boys.

00:13:14.300 --> 00:13:16.300
They used to play with what?

00:13:16.300 --> 00:13:18.300
With the sheep and goats and so on.

00:13:18.300 --> 00:13:21.300
You know, little children in a little village out there.

00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:22.300
And they used to play.

00:13:22.300 --> 00:13:24.300
And one day, his friend,

00:13:24.300 --> 00:13:27.300
the one who was also his brother,

00:13:27.300 --> 00:13:28.300
his foster brother,

00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:29.300
the one who was being breastfed

00:13:29.300 --> 00:13:31.300
by the same Haleematul Sa'diyah.

00:13:31.300 --> 00:13:33.300
They were playing together

00:13:33.300 --> 00:13:35.300
and two angels came down.

00:13:35.300 --> 00:13:38.300
And the angels came down in white clothing.

00:13:38.300 --> 00:13:41.300
This young boy, both of them saw the angels.

00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:44.300
And the angels put Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:13:44.300 --> 00:13:45.300
down on his back,

00:13:45.300 --> 00:13:47.300
slit open his chest,

00:13:47.300 --> 00:13:48.300
took out his heart

00:13:48.300 --> 00:13:50.300
and this young boy began to run.

00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:51.300
Run where?

00:13:51.300 --> 00:13:54.300
He ran straight to Haleematul Sa'diyah

00:13:54.300 --> 00:13:57.300
and he began to tell them what's going on.

00:13:57.300 --> 00:13:59.300
In the meantime, the angels had taken out his heart.

00:13:59.300 --> 00:14:03.300
They had brought a bowl, a golden bowl made of gold

00:14:03.300 --> 00:14:04.300
with Zamzam in it.

00:14:04.300 --> 00:14:05.300
For your information,

00:14:05.300 --> 00:14:08.300
the Zamzam had started gushing just before that

00:14:08.300 --> 00:14:11.300
because it was there from the time of Ismail alaihi wasallam

00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:12.300
but it was clogged

00:14:12.300 --> 00:14:14.300
and it was re-dugged by Abdul Muttalib

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:16.300
as we learnt yesterday.

00:14:16.300 --> 00:14:19.300
And now the same water was being used to purify.

00:14:19.300 --> 00:14:21.300
Purify the heart from what?

00:14:21.300 --> 00:14:25.300
Jealousy, hatred, deception, pride

00:14:25.300 --> 00:14:27.300
and all these bad qualities,

00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:29.300
the quality of anger for the wrong reasons.

00:14:29.300 --> 00:14:31.300
Remember, when we become upset,

00:14:31.300 --> 00:14:33.300
we can become upset for the sake of Allah.

00:14:33.300 --> 00:14:34.300
But a lot of the time,

00:14:34.300 --> 00:14:36.300
it's just for our own selves.

00:14:36.300 --> 00:14:38.300
Whereas Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:14:38.300 --> 00:14:40.300
it is reported by Aisha radiallahu anha,

00:14:40.300 --> 00:14:41.300
she says,

00:14:41.300 --> 00:14:46.300
He never ever sought revenge for himself.

00:14:46.300 --> 00:14:48.300
He didn't get angry because someone wronged him

00:14:48.300 --> 00:14:53.300
but he always did so when someone obviously went against

00:14:53.300 --> 00:14:56.300
the law and command of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:14:56.300 --> 00:14:58.300
it would make him upset.

00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:00.300
And whenever he sought revenge and retaliation,

00:15:00.300 --> 00:15:02.300
it was solely for the sake of Allah,

00:15:02.300 --> 00:15:03.300
not never for himself.

00:15:03.300 --> 00:15:06.300
With us, sake of Allah, we can leave it to go by,

00:15:06.300 --> 00:15:08.300
but for ourselves, we won't let it go by.

00:15:08.300 --> 00:15:11.300
I'm going to fix him, whether now or tomorrow,

00:15:11.300 --> 00:15:13.300
but you're going to see what I'm going to do to him.

00:15:13.300 --> 00:15:14.300
Allah protect us.

00:15:14.300 --> 00:15:17.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala soften our hearts.

00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:19.300
Remember, it's shaitan who wants you

00:15:19.300 --> 00:15:20.300
to continue the circle.

00:15:20.300 --> 00:15:22.300
You do, he does.

00:15:22.300 --> 00:15:24.300
He does back, you do again and so on.

00:15:24.300 --> 00:15:26.300
And it carries on and on for years on end,

00:15:26.300 --> 00:15:27.300
just like the Jahiliyya.

00:15:27.300 --> 00:15:30.300
So Muhammad salallahu alaihi wasallam was purified,

00:15:30.300 --> 00:15:31.300
the heart was replaced,

00:15:31.300 --> 00:15:34.300
a little vein was taken from the back,

00:15:34.300 --> 00:15:36.300
just from the left side and the back,

00:15:36.300 --> 00:15:37.300
and it was removed.

00:15:37.300 --> 00:15:40.300
And this was as Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:15:40.300 --> 00:15:42.300
explains in one narration, he says,

00:15:42.300 --> 00:15:44.300
you see shaitan is like a little frog

00:15:44.300 --> 00:15:46.300
here on your left side.

00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:48.300
Whenever you are engaged

00:15:48.300 --> 00:15:50.300
in the remembrance of Allah,

00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:51.300
shaitan is silent.

00:15:51.300 --> 00:15:53.300
And the minute you are oblivious

00:15:53.300 --> 00:15:55.300
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:15:55.300 --> 00:15:57.300
he begins to whisper in your ear.

00:15:57.300 --> 00:15:58.300
Starts whispering what?

00:15:58.300 --> 00:15:59.300
Anything and everything

00:15:59.300 --> 00:16:01.300
to start doing wrong and you know,

00:16:01.300 --> 00:16:03.300
divulge you like people read Salah,

00:16:03.300 --> 00:16:05.300
and you know a man reading Salah one day,

00:16:05.300 --> 00:16:07.300
he says 250.

00:16:07.300 --> 00:16:09.300
What do you mean 250?

00:16:09.300 --> 00:16:11.300
Oh, okay, I mean Salah, sorry.

00:16:11.300 --> 00:16:14.300
He was busy calculating what people owed him.

00:16:14.300 --> 00:16:15.300
Allahu Akbar.

00:16:15.300 --> 00:16:16.300
Because why? In Salah,

00:16:16.300 --> 00:16:18.300
we busy thinking of everything else.

00:16:18.300 --> 00:16:19.300
What am I going to do after Salah?

00:16:19.300 --> 00:16:20.300
People are saying,

00:16:20.300 --> 00:16:21.300
there's a bray on tonight,

00:16:21.300 --> 00:16:23.300
this sheikh is taking too long, come on.

00:16:23.300 --> 00:16:25.300
Taraweeh is finishing 9 o'clock, imagine.

00:16:25.300 --> 00:16:27.300
And another 7 minutes for wither.

00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:28.300
What's going on here, man?

00:16:28.300 --> 00:16:29.300
Subhanallah.

00:16:29.300 --> 00:16:31.300
That goes through our minds

00:16:31.300 --> 00:16:33.300
because we are oblivious of Allah.

00:16:33.300 --> 00:16:34.300
You take out that shaitan,

00:16:34.300 --> 00:16:35.300
a little frog from there,

00:16:35.300 --> 00:16:36.300
throw him out.

00:16:36.300 --> 00:16:37.300
Allahu Akbar.

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:38.300
How do you throw him out?

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:40.300
By continuing to remember Allah.

00:16:40.300 --> 00:16:41.300
Thank Allah.

00:16:41.300 --> 00:16:42.300
He is giving you an opportunity

00:16:42.300 --> 00:16:45.300
that you may never ever get again.

00:16:45.300 --> 00:16:47.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:16:47.300 --> 00:16:49.300
bless us all and grant us goodness.

00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:51.300
So when that vein was taken

00:16:51.300 --> 00:16:53.300
and it is reported that

00:16:53.300 --> 00:16:55.300
there was now a seal of prophethood there.

00:16:55.300 --> 00:16:56.300
What was it?

00:16:56.300 --> 00:16:58.300
It was a mark here,

00:16:58.300 --> 00:17:00.300
a little like a pea,

00:17:00.300 --> 00:17:02.300
the size of a small pea here

00:17:02.300 --> 00:17:04.300
on his back.

00:17:04.300 --> 00:17:06.300
And it had a few hairs,

00:17:06.300 --> 00:17:08.300
like a mole we would say today.

00:17:08.300 --> 00:17:10.300
It had a little bit of like a mark

00:17:10.300 --> 00:17:12.300
and it had a few hairs that grew out of it.

00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:13.300
Subhanallah.

00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:17.300
And this was in a specific place on his back.

00:17:17.300 --> 00:17:19.300
And Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:17:19.300 --> 00:17:21.300
as Haleematu Sa'diyya and them

00:17:21.300 --> 00:17:23.300
rushed out to see what was going on.

00:17:23.300 --> 00:17:25.300
He was sitting there pale.

00:17:25.300 --> 00:17:26.300
Everything was over obviously.

00:17:26.300 --> 00:17:27.300
And they asked him what happened

00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:29.300
and he narrated the story.

00:17:29.300 --> 00:17:30.300
Now they got worried.

00:17:30.300 --> 00:17:32.300
They were worried for his life.

00:17:32.300 --> 00:17:35.300
Because you see even prior to this,

00:17:35.300 --> 00:17:37.300
the grandfather was told so much.

00:17:37.300 --> 00:17:41.300
The mother had a few signs here and there.

00:17:41.300 --> 00:17:43.300
Not a direct piece of information.

00:17:43.300 --> 00:17:44.300
Some people say the angel Jibreel

00:17:44.300 --> 00:17:45.300
came to the mother.

00:17:45.300 --> 00:17:46.300
No, that's wrong.

00:17:46.300 --> 00:17:48.300
The angel Jibreel alayhi salatu wasalaam

00:17:48.300 --> 00:17:49.300
did not come to the mother

00:17:49.300 --> 00:17:51.300
of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasalaam.

00:17:51.300 --> 00:17:52.300
But there were other signs

00:17:52.300 --> 00:17:54.300
which were lesser signs

00:17:54.300 --> 00:17:55.300
to prove that this man

00:17:55.300 --> 00:17:57.300
is going to be someone important.

00:17:57.300 --> 00:17:59.300
You know like nowadays we see a youngster

00:17:59.300 --> 00:18:00.300
very very intelligent.

00:18:00.300 --> 00:18:02.300
We say watch this page.

00:18:02.300 --> 00:18:03.300
Watch this space.

00:18:03.300 --> 00:18:04.300
That's what some people say.

00:18:04.300 --> 00:18:05.300
Look at this young boy.

00:18:05.300 --> 00:18:07.300
He's going to be very important inshallah.

00:18:07.300 --> 00:18:08.300
He's going to be a big man inshallah.

00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:10.300
He's going to come and something inshallah

00:18:10.300 --> 00:18:11.300
big will happen.

00:18:11.300 --> 00:18:12.300
We're just guessing.

00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:14.300
But in that case, no guessing.

00:18:14.300 --> 00:18:15.300
It was something that was coming.

00:18:15.300 --> 00:18:17.300
Sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:18:17.300 --> 00:18:20.300
So they took him and what did they do?

00:18:20.300 --> 00:18:21.300
They returned him.

00:18:21.300 --> 00:18:23.300
They went back to Makkah.

00:18:23.300 --> 00:18:24.300
And they saw the mother.

00:18:24.300 --> 00:18:25.300
And they saw the grandfather.

00:18:25.300 --> 00:18:27.300
And they said we are returning

00:18:27.300 --> 00:18:28.300
this young boy.

00:18:28.300 --> 00:18:29.300
But why?

00:18:29.300 --> 00:18:30.300
No, we are busy.

00:18:30.300 --> 00:18:31.300
We have this.

00:18:31.300 --> 00:18:32.300
No, no, no.

00:18:32.300 --> 00:18:33.300
Tell us the reason.

00:18:33.300 --> 00:18:34.300
No, we have this excuse.

00:18:34.300 --> 00:18:35.300
No, no, no.

00:18:35.300 --> 00:18:37.300
Tell us why is it

00:18:37.300 --> 00:18:39.300
that you are bringing this child back.

00:18:39.300 --> 00:18:40.300
And then she says,

00:18:40.300 --> 00:18:42.300
well this is what happened.

00:18:42.300 --> 00:18:43.300
There was the angels

00:18:43.300 --> 00:18:45.300
or someone came down.

00:18:45.300 --> 00:18:48.300
They slipped the chest.

00:18:48.300 --> 00:18:50.300
And there was a mark

00:18:50.300 --> 00:18:52.300
that was left on the chest.

00:18:52.300 --> 00:18:53.300
Subhanallah.

00:18:53.300 --> 00:18:55.300
Which remained up to the end.

00:18:55.300 --> 00:18:57.300
And Anas ibn Malik radiallahu anhu

00:18:57.300 --> 00:18:59.300
says I used to see the mark

00:18:59.300 --> 00:19:02.300
left by that cutting of the chest

00:19:02.300 --> 00:19:03.300
from the angels.

00:19:03.300 --> 00:19:04.300
Subhanallah.

00:19:04.300 --> 00:19:06.300
Later on even in the life of Muhammad

00:19:06.300 --> 00:19:07.300
sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:08.300
A little mark.

00:19:08.300 --> 00:19:10.300
Sometimes we have operations.

00:19:10.300 --> 00:19:12.300
And then you have the visible mark

00:19:12.300 --> 00:19:13.300
for a long long time.

00:19:13.300 --> 00:19:15.300
This only Allah knows exactly how it was.

00:19:15.300 --> 00:19:16.300
But there was a mark.

00:19:16.300 --> 00:19:17.300
Subhanallah.

00:19:17.300 --> 00:19:20.300
So what could Amina do?

00:19:20.300 --> 00:19:21.300
Binti Wahab.

00:19:21.300 --> 00:19:23.300
She accepted her child back.

00:19:23.300 --> 00:19:24.300
Looked after the child

00:19:24.300 --> 00:19:26.300
with the assistance of whom?

00:19:26.300 --> 00:19:28.300
With the assistance of Umm Aiman

00:19:28.300 --> 00:19:30.300
who was her slave.

00:19:30.300 --> 00:19:33.300
And she treated the child very well.

00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:34.300
And subhanallah

00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:36.300
it was something amazing.

00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:38.300
They had a beautiful bond

00:19:38.300 --> 00:19:40.300
and this lasted for a few years.

00:19:40.300 --> 00:19:42.300
But before I get into

00:19:42.300 --> 00:19:43.300
the death of the mother

00:19:43.300 --> 00:19:45.300
of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:19:45.300 --> 00:19:47.300
Let me quickly make mention of something

00:19:47.300 --> 00:19:49.300
regarding Iblis.

00:19:49.300 --> 00:19:51.300
There is a narration that makes mention that Iblis

00:19:51.300 --> 00:19:54.300
was moaning four times.

00:19:54.300 --> 00:19:55.300
Moaning, groaning

00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:57.300
even say crying four times.

00:19:57.300 --> 00:19:59.300
He was very arrogant.

00:19:59.300 --> 00:20:01.300
Shaytan, the devil, Satan.

00:20:01.300 --> 00:20:02.300
Very arrogant.

00:20:02.300 --> 00:20:04.300
He was very happy when he transgressed.

00:20:04.300 --> 00:20:07.300
But when Allah cursed him

00:20:07.300 --> 00:20:09.300
he moaned, number one.

00:20:09.300 --> 00:20:11.300
He grunted, very upset.

00:20:11.300 --> 00:20:13.300
Secondly, when he was removed from Jannah

00:20:13.300 --> 00:20:15.300
he was again very upset.

00:20:15.300 --> 00:20:17.300
Thirdly,

00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.300
when Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam was born

00:20:19.300 --> 00:20:20.300
again he moaned, groaned.

00:20:20.300 --> 00:20:22.300
He was very upset again.

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:23.300
And the fourth one was

00:20:23.300 --> 00:20:25.300
when Surah Al-Fatiha was revealed

00:20:25.300 --> 00:20:27.300
it is reported that he moaned and groaned again.

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:29.300
So these were the four times when he moaned and groaned.

00:20:29.300 --> 00:20:31.300
The term used in the Arabic language is

00:20:31.300 --> 00:20:32.300
Ranna.

00:20:32.300 --> 00:20:34.300
Ranna meaning he actually rang.

00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:36.300
You know there was like a sound coming from him

00:20:36.300 --> 00:20:37.300
so upset.

00:20:37.300 --> 00:20:39.300
So these were the four times that Iblis

00:20:39.300 --> 00:20:41.300
was very very upset.

00:20:41.300 --> 00:20:43.300
And then if we take a look at

00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:45.300
the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:20:45.300 --> 00:20:48.710
as his mother

00:20:48.710 --> 00:20:50.710
had relatives in Medina Munawwara

00:20:50.710 --> 00:20:52.710
she used to go there

00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:53.710
now and again.

00:20:53.710 --> 00:20:55.710
The father had passed away in Medina Munawwara

00:20:55.710 --> 00:20:57.710
and as I told you he also

00:20:57.710 --> 00:20:58.710
had relatives there.

00:20:58.710 --> 00:21:00.710
The mother went

00:21:00.710 --> 00:21:02.710
and once on her way back

00:21:02.710 --> 00:21:04.710
she passed away in a place called

00:21:04.710 --> 00:21:05.710
Abwa.

00:21:05.710 --> 00:21:07.710
And she was with her slave girl Um Muayman.

00:21:07.710 --> 00:21:09.710
And Um Muayman took

00:21:09.710 --> 00:21:11.710
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:11.710 --> 00:21:13.710
looked after him,

00:21:13.710 --> 00:21:15.710
cared for him, returned him to Makkah

00:21:15.710 --> 00:21:17.710
and went straight to the grandfather

00:21:17.710 --> 00:21:19.710
whose name was Abdul Muttali.

00:21:19.710 --> 00:21:21.710
How old was Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam?

00:21:21.710 --> 00:21:24.710
When his mother passed away.

00:21:24.710 --> 00:21:26.710
He was six years old

00:21:26.710 --> 00:21:28.710
according to the vast majority of narrations.

00:21:28.710 --> 00:21:30.710
In fact mentioning the date

00:21:30.710 --> 00:21:32.710
of birth which we haven't said yet.

00:21:32.710 --> 00:21:34.710
I just realized we haven't said it yet.

00:21:34.710 --> 00:21:36.710
There are several narrations as to

00:21:36.710 --> 00:21:38.710
the precise date of birth.

00:21:38.710 --> 00:21:40.710
But the majority, the vast

00:21:40.710 --> 00:21:42.710
majority say it was the 12th

00:21:42.710 --> 00:21:44.710
of Rabi' al-Awwal.

00:21:44.710 --> 00:21:45.710
12th of Rabi' al-Awwal.

00:21:45.710 --> 00:21:47.710
Which year was it?

00:21:47.710 --> 00:21:49.710
Now at that time they did not use to

00:21:49.710 --> 00:21:51.710
work things out by years

00:21:51.710 --> 00:21:53.710
as in one, two, three from

00:21:53.710 --> 00:21:55.710
the beginning of time or so on.

00:21:55.710 --> 00:21:57.710
But a major incident

00:21:57.710 --> 00:21:59.710
that occurred, they used

00:21:59.710 --> 00:22:01.710
to work around it. Up to today

00:22:01.710 --> 00:22:03.710
the Christian calendar works around

00:22:03.710 --> 00:22:05.710
some major incident that occurred.

00:22:05.710 --> 00:22:07.710
The Hijri calendar works around

00:22:07.710 --> 00:22:09.710
the Hijra. So at that time the

00:22:09.710 --> 00:22:11.710
major incident that really

00:22:11.710 --> 00:22:13.710
bewildered everybody was the incident

00:22:13.710 --> 00:22:15.710
of the elephants.

00:22:15.710 --> 00:22:17.710
So he was born in the same year

00:22:17.710 --> 00:22:19.710
that that had happened. So it was called

00:22:19.710 --> 00:22:21.710
Aam al-Feel, the year of the elephant.

00:22:21.710 --> 00:22:23.710
And I told you

00:22:23.710 --> 00:22:25.710
the correct narration is that there was

00:22:25.710 --> 00:22:27.710
one elephant, not a whole army of elephants.

00:22:27.710 --> 00:22:29.710
One elephant. And this is mentioned

00:22:29.710 --> 00:22:31.710
even in the Quran, al-Feel,

00:22:31.710 --> 00:22:33.710
one elephant. So if we look

00:22:33.710 --> 00:22:35.710
at this, he was born the year

00:22:35.710 --> 00:22:37.710
of the elephant, 12th

00:22:37.710 --> 00:22:39.710
of Rabi' al-Awwal. And thereafter

00:22:39.710 --> 00:22:41.710
let's go back to

00:22:41.710 --> 00:22:43.710
where Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam's

00:22:43.710 --> 00:22:45.710
mother passed away when he was 6 years old.

00:22:45.710 --> 00:22:47.710
Ummu Ayman took him back

00:22:47.710 --> 00:22:49.710
to the grandfather. The grandfather

00:22:49.710 --> 00:22:51.710
loved him so much.

00:22:51.710 --> 00:22:53.710
And the grandfather treated him better

00:22:53.710 --> 00:22:55.710
than all the other children, so much so

00:22:55.710 --> 00:22:57.710
he had 11 sons,

00:22:57.710 --> 00:22:59.710
Abdul Muttalib.

00:22:59.710 --> 00:23:01.710
And he had, as we mentioned

00:23:01.710 --> 00:23:03.710
yesterday, a place just near the Kaaba

00:23:03.710 --> 00:23:05.710
upon the shade of the Kaaba.

00:23:05.710 --> 00:23:07.710
He had a little carpet laid

00:23:07.710 --> 00:23:09.710
for him, or should we say a little

00:23:09.710 --> 00:23:11.710
sitting place. When we say carpet

00:23:11.710 --> 00:23:13.710
we're thinking of this proper carpet

00:23:13.710 --> 00:23:15.710
that is laid here. No, a different type

00:23:15.710 --> 00:23:17.710
of a carpet of that particular time,

00:23:17.710 --> 00:23:19.710
something to sit on. And that belonged to

00:23:19.710 --> 00:23:21.710
him, no one dare sit on it.

00:23:21.710 --> 00:23:23.710
But when Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:23:23.710 --> 00:23:25.710
now, he was a young boy,

00:23:25.710 --> 00:23:27.710
above the age of 6, between 6 and 8

00:23:27.710 --> 00:23:29.710
years old. And he used to crawl

00:23:29.710 --> 00:23:31.710
there quietly, and he used to get onto it

00:23:31.710 --> 00:23:33.710
and the uncles used to try and get him

00:23:33.710 --> 00:23:35.710
off it. And the grandfather used to say, no,

00:23:35.710 --> 00:23:37.710
let him sit there. And they were like amazed.

00:23:37.710 --> 00:23:39.710
This young, youngsters sitting

00:23:39.710 --> 00:23:41.710
there, we are not even allowed to sit on there.

00:23:41.710 --> 00:23:43.710
But the grandfather used to say,

00:23:43.710 --> 00:23:45.710
this young boy is going to be a leader.

00:23:45.710 --> 00:23:47.710
He's going to be someone

00:23:47.710 --> 00:23:49.710
great, sallallahu alaihi wasallam.

00:23:49.710 --> 00:23:51.710
And he continued to

00:23:51.710 --> 00:23:53.710
say things of this nature. And the

00:23:53.710 --> 00:23:55.710
grandfather

00:23:55.710 --> 00:23:57.710
fell ill at one stage.

00:23:57.710 --> 00:23:59.710
And when the Prophet sallallahu alaihi

00:23:59.710 --> 00:24:01.710
wasallam was 8 years old,

00:24:01.710 --> 00:24:03.710
the grandfather passed away.

00:24:03.710 --> 00:24:05.710
It was a very sad day. Take

00:24:05.710 --> 00:24:07.710
a look, an orphan, with

00:24:07.710 --> 00:24:09.710
no father. Then the mother passes

00:24:09.710 --> 00:24:11.710
away. Thereafter,

00:24:11.710 --> 00:24:13.710
the grandfather passes away. So he

00:24:13.710 --> 00:24:15.710
is being shifted from one to the

00:24:15.710 --> 00:24:17.710
other. He has tasted the

00:24:17.710 --> 00:24:19.710
sadness in his early life.

00:24:19.710 --> 00:24:21.710
Or should I say, the loss of loved ones.

00:24:21.710 --> 00:24:23.710
How many of us have lost loved

00:24:23.710 --> 00:24:25.710
ones? If you have lost loved

00:24:25.710 --> 00:24:27.710
ones, remember one thing. It is

00:24:27.710 --> 00:24:29.710
not a sign of the wrath of Allah sallallahu

00:24:29.710 --> 00:24:31.710
wa ta'ala. It's a sign if you are

00:24:31.710 --> 00:24:33.710
to accept and digest,

00:24:33.710 --> 00:24:35.710
a sign of a gift of Allah sallallahu

00:24:35.710 --> 00:24:37.710
wa ta'ala upon you. Because he has

00:24:37.710 --> 00:24:39.710
favored Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:39.710 --> 00:24:41.710
with the same gift. And even

00:24:41.710 --> 00:24:43.710
more. So we are

00:24:43.710 --> 00:24:45.710
taught that in life,

00:24:45.710 --> 00:24:47.710
you won't always have everything

00:24:47.710 --> 00:24:49.710
rosy. No! Today we heard

00:24:49.710 --> 00:24:51.710
a beautiful verse that was recited in

00:24:51.710 --> 00:24:53.710
Taraweeh.

00:24:53.710 --> 00:25:05.710
You will

00:25:05.710 --> 00:25:07.710
definitely hear a lot of

00:25:07.710 --> 00:25:09.710
bad words. You will have

00:25:09.710 --> 00:25:11.710
to bear a lot regarding

00:25:11.710 --> 00:25:13.710
the statements of those who are

00:25:13.710 --> 00:25:15.710
polytheists and the people of the book.

00:25:15.710 --> 00:25:17.710
And this is why as Muslimin,

00:25:17.710 --> 00:25:19.710
Allah sallallahu wa ta'ala tells us

00:25:19.710 --> 00:25:21.710
if you bear patience, then that is the best

00:25:21.710 --> 00:25:23.710
thing you could do. Today,

00:25:23.710 --> 00:25:25.710
people laugh at us. You want to grow a beard,

00:25:25.710 --> 00:25:27.710
you want to wear your hijab, you want to dress

00:25:27.710 --> 00:25:29.710
as a Muslim, you want to fulfill your

00:25:29.710 --> 00:25:31.710
Salah. Anything to do with the

00:25:31.710 --> 00:25:33.710
religion. You want to be a Muslim.

00:25:33.710 --> 00:25:35.710
And the people around you make it difficult

00:25:35.710 --> 00:25:37.710
for you. May Allah sallallahu wa ta'ala

00:25:37.710 --> 00:25:39.710
safeguard us. So we were not promised that

00:25:39.710 --> 00:25:41.710
you are going to have a simple, easy

00:25:41.710 --> 00:25:43.710
go life. But you will have

00:25:43.710 --> 00:25:45.710
tests upon tests. The more tests

00:25:45.710 --> 00:25:47.710
you have, the more opportunities for you to

00:25:47.710 --> 00:25:49.710
pass. The more you pass, the greater

00:25:49.710 --> 00:25:51.710
the rank you will have in Paradise. So

00:25:51.710 --> 00:25:53.710
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam had the highest

00:25:53.710 --> 00:25:55.710
rank and he achieved it in many

00:25:55.710 --> 00:25:57.710
different ways. Chosen by Allah

00:25:57.710 --> 00:25:59.710
sallallahu wa ta'ala and his reaction

00:25:59.710 --> 00:26:01.710
was the best reaction possible

00:26:01.710 --> 00:26:03.710
for those particular difficulties

00:26:03.710 --> 00:26:05.710
that he had gone through. Look,

00:26:05.710 --> 00:26:07.710
lost a father, lost a mother,

00:26:07.710 --> 00:26:09.710
lost a grandfather. And thereafter,

00:26:09.710 --> 00:26:11.710
what happened?

00:26:11.710 --> 00:26:13.710
Well, his uncle took

00:26:13.710 --> 00:26:15.710
over. Which uncle? Abu Talib.

00:26:15.710 --> 00:26:17.710
And Abu Talib had other children

00:26:17.710 --> 00:26:19.710
as well. Abu Talib was

00:26:19.710 --> 00:26:21.710
a young uncle of his.

00:26:21.710 --> 00:26:23.710
And he had

00:26:23.710 --> 00:26:25.710
so many other children, he used to look after

00:26:25.710 --> 00:26:27.710
them. But he loved this

00:26:27.710 --> 00:26:29.710
little nephew. He loved him so much.

00:26:29.710 --> 00:26:31.710
Allah placed the love in the heart

00:26:31.710 --> 00:26:33.710
of the

00:26:33.710 --> 00:26:35.710
uncle and the grandfather before

00:26:35.710 --> 00:26:37.710
him. Sometimes you look at a child

00:26:37.710 --> 00:26:39.710
and you cannot help

00:26:39.710 --> 00:26:41.710
but love the child. The way they talk

00:26:41.710 --> 00:26:43.710
to you. The way they look at you.

00:26:43.710 --> 00:26:45.710
The way they carry themselves. Subhanallah.

00:26:45.710 --> 00:26:47.710
It's placed by Allah sallallahu wa ta'ala.

00:26:47.710 --> 00:26:49.710
And sometimes you look at someone

00:26:49.710 --> 00:26:51.710
and you just want to look away

00:26:51.710 --> 00:26:53.710
because of the way they act and they behave

00:26:53.710 --> 00:26:55.710
and the way they carry themselves and

00:26:55.710 --> 00:26:57.710
so on. So it's Allah sallallahu wa ta'ala

00:26:57.710 --> 00:26:59.710
who really does that

00:26:59.710 --> 00:27:01.710
where He puts it in your heart to love

00:27:01.710 --> 00:27:03.710
and He puts it in your heart to turn away.

00:27:03.710 --> 00:27:05.710
So this uncle,

00:27:05.710 --> 00:27:07.710
he noticed that he didn't

00:27:07.710 --> 00:27:09.710
have much wealth. But ever since

00:27:09.710 --> 00:27:11.710
he began to look after this young

00:27:11.710 --> 00:27:13.710
boy, there was so much blessing, so much

00:27:13.710 --> 00:27:15.710
baraka. And he

00:27:15.710 --> 00:27:17.710
found that he watched the

00:27:17.710 --> 00:27:19.710
children as they ate. When

00:27:19.710 --> 00:27:21.710
the little children came to eat all his own

00:27:21.710 --> 00:27:23.710
children, they would all go and try and snatch

00:27:23.710 --> 00:27:25.710
the best of pieces of food and so on.

00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:27.710
And this young boy came, he sat, he waited

00:27:27.710 --> 00:27:29.710
and he knew that what was a

00:27:29.710 --> 00:27:31.710
portion for him, he would get it so he

00:27:31.710 --> 00:27:33.710
waited and then he would take

00:27:33.710 --> 00:27:35.710
like an adult already from that

00:27:35.710 --> 00:27:37.710
age. Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:27:37.710 --> 00:27:39.710
So Allah sallallahu wa ta'ala

00:27:39.710 --> 00:27:41.710
had

00:27:41.710 --> 00:27:43.710
this perfect upbringing for

00:27:43.710 --> 00:27:45.710
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:27:45.710 --> 00:27:47.710
But perfect from which angle?

00:27:47.710 --> 00:27:49.710
Not from the angle of him having a father

00:27:49.710 --> 00:27:51.710
and a mother and so on and so forth, but

00:27:51.710 --> 00:27:53.710
his credentials were never dented

00:27:53.710 --> 00:27:55.710
from the very beginning. From infancy,

00:27:55.710 --> 00:27:57.710
nothing to say this

00:27:57.710 --> 00:27:59.710
man is a liar, he's a cheat, he had

00:27:59.710 --> 00:28:01.710
bad manners, morals, he was

00:28:01.710 --> 00:28:03.710
wrong in this way, that way, he had bad company

00:28:03.710 --> 00:28:05.710
never ever. Subhanallah.

00:28:05.710 --> 00:28:07.710
He was powerful from

00:28:07.710 --> 00:28:09.710
that early age already, preparation

00:28:09.710 --> 00:28:11.710
for sending him to the people of Makkah

00:28:11.710 --> 00:28:13.710
in a way that they won't have

00:28:13.710 --> 00:28:15.710
a response unless

00:28:15.710 --> 00:28:17.710
they are to accept. That is

00:28:17.710 --> 00:28:19.710
the only response they could have had.

00:28:19.710 --> 00:28:21.710
Anything else would be out of their arrogance

00:28:21.710 --> 00:28:23.710
because they know the man and they

00:28:23.710 --> 00:28:25.710
know him from his birth and they

00:28:25.710 --> 00:28:27.710
know how high in character,

00:28:27.710 --> 00:28:29.710
conduct and morals he always was.

00:28:29.710 --> 00:28:31.710
So Muhammad sallallahu alayhi

00:28:31.710 --> 00:28:33.710
wa sallam grew up in this

00:28:33.710 --> 00:28:35.710
house full of

00:28:35.710 --> 00:28:37.710
humbleness, humility

00:28:37.710 --> 00:28:39.710
and he used to go out to look after

00:28:39.710 --> 00:28:41.710
the sheep

00:28:41.710 --> 00:28:43.710
and the goats.

00:28:43.710 --> 00:28:45.710
And we made mention of this very briefly

00:28:45.710 --> 00:28:47.710
yesterday, but I'd like to repeat it.

00:28:47.710 --> 00:28:49.710
Sheep and goats,

00:28:49.710 --> 00:28:51.710
all the Prophets of Allah

00:28:51.710 --> 00:28:53.710
subhanahu wa ta'ala looked after these

00:28:53.710 --> 00:28:55.710
and some of the

00:28:55.710 --> 00:28:57.710
benefits were to instill

00:28:57.710 --> 00:28:59.710
within this human being

00:28:59.710 --> 00:29:01.710
who was being prepared to come out

00:29:01.710 --> 00:29:03.710
as a Prophet, lots of patience.

00:29:03.710 --> 00:29:05.710
With animals you need

00:29:05.710 --> 00:29:07.710
so much patience because you can't even

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:11.220
talk to them. Subhanallah.

00:29:11.220 --> 00:29:13.220
And thereafter, humbleness,

00:29:13.220 --> 00:29:15.220
humility because

00:29:15.220 --> 00:29:17.220
you've got to do so much and you

00:29:17.220 --> 00:29:19.220
are down to earth, your clothes

00:29:19.220 --> 00:29:21.220
are messed, sometimes you have to clean,

00:29:21.220 --> 00:29:23.220
sometimes you walk over that which is

00:29:23.220 --> 00:29:25.220
unclean and so on. And a lot

00:29:25.220 --> 00:29:27.220
of humbleness is also achieved

00:29:27.220 --> 00:29:29.220
by this. And at the same

00:29:29.220 --> 00:29:31.220
time you will find that

00:29:31.220 --> 00:29:33.220
over and above the patience

00:29:33.220 --> 00:29:35.220
and the humbleness there is dedication.

00:29:35.220 --> 00:29:37.220
When one little animal is

00:29:37.220 --> 00:29:39.220
out, away from the rest of the flock,

00:29:39.220 --> 00:29:41.220
you find the shepherd will always

00:29:41.220 --> 00:29:43.220
make an effort to go and get it.

00:29:43.220 --> 00:29:45.220
You don't just leave one. And then

00:29:45.220 --> 00:29:47.220
you develop a link with these animals.

00:29:47.220 --> 00:29:49.220
And even though you cannot

00:29:49.220 --> 00:29:51.220
communicate properly with them,

00:29:51.220 --> 00:29:53.220
they understand you to a certain extent

00:29:53.220 --> 00:29:55.220
and you begin to understand them.

00:29:55.220 --> 00:29:57.220
Then you lose one. One might die,

00:29:57.220 --> 00:29:59.220
a few might die, something might happen

00:29:59.220 --> 00:30:01.220
to one and the other one, something else

00:30:01.220 --> 00:30:03.220
might happen to it, one may be stolen

00:30:03.220 --> 00:30:05.220
and so on. All this is part of the training

00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:07.220
with full humbleness

00:30:07.220 --> 00:30:09.220
and humility.

00:30:09.220 --> 00:30:11.220
With us, when

00:30:11.220 --> 00:30:13.220
someone tries to put us into a difficult

00:30:13.220 --> 00:30:15.220
situation, we get upset,

00:30:15.220 --> 00:30:17.220
we get angry, not realizing, ya Allah!

00:30:17.220 --> 00:30:19.220
You are the one who chose this for me.

00:30:19.220 --> 00:30:21.220
Perhaps you are preparing me for something

00:30:21.220 --> 00:30:23.220
greater. Perhaps there is something

00:30:23.220 --> 00:30:25.220
to come in my life that you have

00:30:25.220 --> 00:30:27.220
now made easy for me from

00:30:27.220 --> 00:30:29.220
the training that I'm receiving

00:30:29.220 --> 00:30:31.220
now. May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant

00:30:31.220 --> 00:30:33.220
us ease. So

00:30:33.220 --> 00:30:35.220
Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi

00:30:35.220 --> 00:30:37.220
wa sallam,

00:30:37.220 --> 00:30:39.220
he was taken by

00:30:39.220 --> 00:30:41.220
his uncle, sometimes

00:30:41.220 --> 00:30:43.220
on some of the journeys

00:30:43.220 --> 00:30:45.220
that they went

00:30:45.220 --> 00:30:47.220
with the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam.

00:30:47.220 --> 00:30:49.220
And they used to have, as we mentioned,

00:30:49.220 --> 00:30:51.220
rihlatul shita'i wa al-saifi.

00:30:51.220 --> 00:30:53.220
So when they were coming down

00:30:53.220 --> 00:30:55.220
to Yemen once,

00:30:55.220 --> 00:30:57.220
they were coming down to Yemen

00:30:57.220 --> 00:30:59.220
in the winter with

00:30:59.220 --> 00:31:01.220
a caravan.

00:31:01.220 --> 00:31:03.220
And what happened is, Muhammad sallallahu

00:31:03.220 --> 00:31:05.220
alaihi wa sallam was a young man,

00:31:05.220 --> 00:31:07.220
young boy, in his early

00:31:07.220 --> 00:31:09.220
teens.

00:31:09.220 --> 00:31:11.220
And as they settled

00:31:11.220 --> 00:31:13.220
down in one area, a huge

00:31:13.220 --> 00:31:15.220
camel came charging

00:31:15.220 --> 00:31:17.220
for the whole group. And they

00:31:17.220 --> 00:31:19.220
all scattered and went away. And

00:31:19.220 --> 00:31:21.220
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam was standing there

00:31:21.220 --> 00:31:23.220
alone. And as it

00:31:23.220 --> 00:31:25.220
came, he just stood there. Everyone

00:31:25.220 --> 00:31:27.220
had run. And when it came to

00:31:27.220 --> 00:31:29.220
him, it stopped, suddenly.

00:31:29.220 --> 00:31:31.220
It sat down.

00:31:31.220 --> 00:31:33.220
And Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam put his

00:31:33.220 --> 00:31:35.220
hand on it

00:31:35.220 --> 00:31:37.220
and calmed it down.

00:31:37.220 --> 00:31:39.220
And then jumped on it and rode

00:31:39.220 --> 00:31:41.220
it to where they were. They were shocked.

00:31:41.220 --> 00:31:43.220
Subhanallah. What a sign.

00:31:43.220 --> 00:31:45.220
This man has calmed down

00:31:45.220 --> 00:31:47.220
even the animal. Do you know

00:31:47.220 --> 00:31:49.220
there is a story of Fudala.

00:31:49.220 --> 00:31:51.220
Fudala was a man who intended

00:31:51.220 --> 00:31:53.220
to kill Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:31:53.220 --> 00:31:55.220
in Hunayn. And what did he do?

00:31:55.220 --> 00:31:57.220
He was one of the Bedouin Arabs who was

00:31:57.220 --> 00:31:59.220
a marksman, sharp man.

00:31:59.220 --> 00:32:01.220
He took a

00:32:01.220 --> 00:32:03.220
a pointed knife which was

00:32:03.220 --> 00:32:05.220
jagged, which would slit anyone.

00:32:05.220 --> 00:32:07.220
And there, they had no value

00:32:07.220 --> 00:32:09.220
for life of people.

00:32:09.220 --> 00:32:11.220
Especially at war.

00:32:11.220 --> 00:32:13.220
So Hunayn was later on in the

00:32:13.220 --> 00:32:15.220
time of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam's life. It is

00:32:15.220 --> 00:32:17.220
reported that 11 times they tried

00:32:17.220 --> 00:32:19.220
to murder him. And 11 times Allah

00:32:19.220 --> 00:32:21.220
sallallahu alaihi wa sallam saved him.

00:32:21.220 --> 00:32:23.220
So one of the times, Fudala

00:32:23.220 --> 00:32:25.220
what did he do? He pretended

00:32:25.220 --> 00:32:27.220
to be a Muslim and he joined the Muslim army

00:32:27.220 --> 00:32:29.220
in Hunayn. And he

00:32:29.220 --> 00:32:31.220
was waiting, waiting for which opportunity.

00:32:31.220 --> 00:32:33.220
When I see a good opportunity

00:32:33.220 --> 00:32:35.220
I'll slit this man's belly open and it's

00:32:35.220 --> 00:32:37.220
over. So as he went

00:32:37.220 --> 00:32:39.220
Nabi sallallahu alaihi wa sallam turned and looked at him.

00:32:39.220 --> 00:32:41.220
Fudala. Nabi sallallahu

00:32:41.220 --> 00:32:43.220
alaihi wa sallam put his hand on the chest

00:32:43.220 --> 00:32:45.220
of Fudala and looked in his eyes.

00:32:45.220 --> 00:32:47.220
And do you know what happened? Fudala

00:32:47.220 --> 00:32:49.220
says, instantly my

00:32:49.220 --> 00:32:51.220
heart was filled with love

00:32:51.220 --> 00:32:53.220
for this man, instantly,

00:32:53.220 --> 00:32:55.220
instantaneously. And he

00:32:55.220 --> 00:32:57.220
says, he asked me, he says

00:32:57.220 --> 00:32:59.220
Oh Fudala, what is

00:32:59.220 --> 00:33:01.220
it that you want?

00:33:01.220 --> 00:33:03.220
So he says astaghfirullah. Obviously

00:33:03.220 --> 00:33:05.220
now he's repenting here. What is

00:33:05.220 --> 00:33:07.220
it you want? He said Ya Rasulallah

00:33:07.220 --> 00:33:09.220
I came with the intention

00:33:09.220 --> 00:33:11.220
to kill you but I bear witness that

00:33:11.220 --> 00:33:13.220
there is none worthy of worship besides Allah

00:33:13.220 --> 00:33:15.220
and you are indeed a messenger of Allah

00:33:15.220 --> 00:33:17.220
sallallahu alaihi wa sallam. Imagine.

00:33:17.220 --> 00:33:19.220
This was a story that happened later on

00:33:19.220 --> 00:33:21.220
in the life of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wa sallam.

00:33:21.220 --> 00:33:23.220
So the animals also

00:33:23.220 --> 00:33:25.220
subhanallah. In fact, so

00:33:25.220 --> 00:33:27.220
much so, it brings tears to the eyes

00:33:27.220 --> 00:33:29.220
when we think of a hadith where

00:33:29.220 --> 00:33:31.220
the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam says

00:33:31.220 --> 00:33:33.220
إِمِّ لَأَعْرِفُ حَجَرًا بِمَكَّةَ

00:33:33.220 --> 00:33:35.220
كَانَ يُسَلِّمُ عَلَيْهِ

00:33:35.220 --> 00:33:37.220
He says, I actually know a

00:33:37.220 --> 00:33:39.220
rocking Makkah that used to greet me.

00:33:39.220 --> 00:33:41.220
Allahu Akbar. The

00:33:41.220 --> 00:33:43.220
rocking Makkah used to greet him

00:33:43.220 --> 00:33:45.220
sallallahu alaihi wa sallam.

00:33:45.220 --> 00:33:47.220
May Allah

00:33:47.220 --> 00:33:49.220
grant us the ability

00:33:49.220 --> 00:33:51.220
to understand how fortunate we are

00:33:51.220 --> 00:33:53.220
to be following such a powerful message

00:33:53.220 --> 00:33:55.220
of the most powerful of all messengers.

00:33:55.220 --> 00:33:57.220
Many of us take it for granted.

00:33:57.220 --> 00:33:59.220
It's about time we did something about it

00:33:59.220 --> 00:34:01.220
and it's about time we learn. This is the man

00:34:01.220 --> 00:34:03.220
through whom inshallah we will be

00:34:03.220 --> 00:34:05.220
entering Jannah. He has been granted the

00:34:05.220 --> 00:34:07.220
power to intercede. May Allah grant that to us.

00:34:07.220 --> 00:34:11.040
And we would like

00:34:11.040 --> 00:34:13.040
for us to be recognized on that day

00:34:13.040 --> 00:34:15.040
as part of his Ummah.

00:34:15.040 --> 00:34:17.040
So the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:34:17.040 --> 00:34:19.040
on another journey when he was going up

00:34:19.040 --> 00:34:21.040
to Asham, the Syrian region as

00:34:21.040 --> 00:34:23.040
we would call it today. But not only

00:34:23.040 --> 00:34:25.040
the country of Syria, it would include Lebanon

00:34:25.040 --> 00:34:27.040
as well as Palestine and some areas

00:34:27.040 --> 00:34:29.040
there. When they were heading up north

00:34:29.040 --> 00:34:31.040
they used to stop at a certain monastery

00:34:31.040 --> 00:34:33.040
with the caravans. And when they

00:34:33.040 --> 00:34:35.040
stopped at one monastery, what happened is

00:34:35.040 --> 00:34:37.040
amazing.

00:34:37.040 --> 00:34:40.320
The monk never

00:34:40.320 --> 00:34:42.320
ever came out to meet these people.

00:34:42.320 --> 00:34:44.320
His name was Bahira

00:34:44.320 --> 00:34:46.320
or Buhira, depending on how you want to

00:34:46.320 --> 00:34:48.320
pronounce it. He never used to come out

00:34:48.320 --> 00:34:50.320
but that day

00:34:50.320 --> 00:34:52.320
he saw something and he came out

00:34:52.320 --> 00:34:54.320
to greet them. And he started greeting

00:34:54.320 --> 00:34:56.320
them and he asked who is this man? Who is

00:34:56.320 --> 00:34:58.320
this young boy? And they told him this and this

00:34:58.320 --> 00:35:00.320
so he called the guardian and he said

00:35:00.320 --> 00:35:02.320
watch this young boy. Be

00:35:02.320 --> 00:35:04.320
careful. He is going to be someone

00:35:04.320 --> 00:35:06.320
and be careful. Be careful of

00:35:06.320 --> 00:35:08.320
the Jews. This is his statement. It's mentioned

00:35:08.320 --> 00:35:10.320
in the books of history because they are a very

00:35:10.320 --> 00:35:12.320
jealous nation.

00:35:12.320 --> 00:35:14.320
This is what he says himself, the monk.

00:35:14.320 --> 00:35:16.320
And thereafter

00:35:16.320 --> 00:35:18.320
he decided to go in and prepare a meal

00:35:18.320 --> 00:35:20.320
and so on. And when they were preparing a meal

00:35:20.320 --> 00:35:22.320
everyone sat down

00:35:22.320 --> 00:35:24.320
and he says where is this young boy?

00:35:24.320 --> 00:35:26.320
They said no he is out there with the animals. Call him

00:35:26.320 --> 00:35:28.320
call him. And as they called him

00:35:28.320 --> 00:35:30.320
something strange happened. What happened?

00:35:30.320 --> 00:35:32.320
Everyone was already sitting in the shade

00:35:32.320 --> 00:35:34.320
of the tree.

00:35:34.320 --> 00:35:36.320
And the monk noticed that when

00:35:36.320 --> 00:35:38.320
this young boy came there was no shade left

00:35:38.320 --> 00:35:40.320
so he sat down and the

00:35:40.320 --> 00:35:42.320
tree turned. Slightly

00:35:42.320 --> 00:35:44.320
and it shaded him.

00:35:44.320 --> 00:35:46.320
And he says look at this. Look at this.

00:35:46.320 --> 00:35:48.320
It's a sign.

00:35:48.320 --> 00:35:50.320
This is the young boy.

00:35:50.320 --> 00:35:52.320
This is the boy. He will be sent one day.

00:35:52.320 --> 00:35:54.320
Now the details are coming out.

00:35:54.320 --> 00:35:56.320
This was the first incident

00:35:56.320 --> 00:35:58.320
where there was one of the most direct

00:35:58.320 --> 00:36:00.320
pointers at this

00:36:00.320 --> 00:36:02.320
young man being a messenger

00:36:02.320 --> 00:36:04.320
of Allah. For your information

00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:06.320
this was one of the first incidents

00:36:06.320 --> 00:36:08.320
or the first incident

00:36:08.320 --> 00:36:10.320
where there was a direct pointer

00:36:10.320 --> 00:36:12.320
in that particular direction.

00:36:12.320 --> 00:36:14.320
And this was by a monk.

00:36:14.320 --> 00:36:16.320
And this is why we say the people of

00:36:16.320 --> 00:36:18.320
the book, not all of them

00:36:18.320 --> 00:36:20.320
had changed the books and so on. There were

00:36:20.320 --> 00:36:22.320
some who were honest. Like Allah

00:36:22.320 --> 00:36:24.320
subhanahu wa ta'ala has mentioned in the Quran

00:36:24.320 --> 00:36:26.320
that some of those they believed

00:36:26.320 --> 00:36:28.320
they did not hide the verses

00:36:28.320 --> 00:36:30.320
and they said it

00:36:30.320 --> 00:36:32.320
outward, openly. Like we will see

00:36:32.320 --> 00:36:34.320
later on Waraka bin Naufal as well

00:36:34.320 --> 00:36:36.320
was one of those who uttered the truth.

00:36:36.320 --> 00:36:38.320
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:36:38.320 --> 00:36:40.320
So this was also a sign.

00:36:40.320 --> 00:36:42.320
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:36:42.320 --> 00:36:44.320
has blessed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi

00:36:44.320 --> 00:36:46.320
wa sallam, the monk told

00:36:46.320 --> 00:36:48.320
Abu Talib to

00:36:48.320 --> 00:36:50.320
take this young boy away.

00:36:50.320 --> 00:36:52.320
He says take this young boy away.

00:36:52.320 --> 00:36:54.320
Let him

00:36:54.320 --> 00:36:56.320
go back. Make sure that he comes

00:36:56.320 --> 00:36:58.320
back and look after him

00:36:58.320 --> 00:37:00.320
carefully. Don't let him travel

00:37:00.320 --> 00:37:02.320
towards the Roman Empire

00:37:02.320 --> 00:37:04.320
up to the Byzantine Empire. No,

00:37:04.320 --> 00:37:06.320
he shouldn't go there. If the Romans get hold of him

00:37:06.320 --> 00:37:08.320
they perhaps will kill him because they wouldn't

00:37:08.320 --> 00:37:10.320
want a messenger to come from amongst

00:37:10.320 --> 00:37:12.320
the Arabs.

00:37:12.320 --> 00:37:14.320
All the messengers have been from them so far.

00:37:14.320 --> 00:37:16.320
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protected

00:37:16.320 --> 00:37:18.320
him and he was returned to Makkatul

00:37:18.320 --> 00:37:20.320
Mukarrama and thereafter safeguarded

00:37:20.320 --> 00:37:22.320
all the time. So much so that when he took

00:37:22.320 --> 00:37:24.320
part in building the Kaaba

00:37:24.320 --> 00:37:26.320
and he had his back open and

00:37:26.320 --> 00:37:28.320
so on, his uncle told him to cover his

00:37:28.320 --> 00:37:30.320
back. Subhanallah. So that he could

00:37:30.320 --> 00:37:32.320
be protected from the stones. But one of the

00:37:32.320 --> 00:37:34.320
underlying reasons was also the

00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:36.320
signs would not be seen by others

00:37:36.320 --> 00:37:38.320
because he had to be

00:37:38.320 --> 00:37:40.320
preserved. Sallallahu alayhi

00:37:40.320 --> 00:37:42.320
wasallam. Little did they know that Allah

00:37:42.320 --> 00:37:44.320
subhanahu wa ta'ala is the

00:37:44.320 --> 00:37:46.320
protector. May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:37:46.320 --> 00:37:48.320
protect every single one of us.

00:37:48.320 --> 00:37:50.320
I'd like to go back to the story of Ummu

00:37:50.320 --> 00:37:52.320
Ayman.

00:37:52.320 --> 00:37:54.320
Very very important person in the Seerah of

00:37:54.320 --> 00:37:56.320
Muhammad Sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:37:56.320 --> 00:37:58.320
When he married Khadija binti Khuwailid

00:37:58.320 --> 00:38:00.320
radiallahu anha, she still looked after him

00:38:00.320 --> 00:38:02.320
meaning she was still serving him.

00:38:02.320 --> 00:38:04.320
And he decided to free her at the time

00:38:04.320 --> 00:38:06.320
because he inherited her from the mother,

00:38:06.320 --> 00:38:08.320
from his own mother. And he freed her

00:38:08.320 --> 00:38:10.320
and later on when Islam

00:38:10.320 --> 00:38:12.320
started and Nubu, a prophet who

00:38:12.320 --> 00:38:14.320
came, one of the first people to accept

00:38:14.320 --> 00:38:16.320
Islam, it is reported she was

00:38:16.320 --> 00:38:18.320
one of the first women after Khadija

00:38:18.320 --> 00:38:20.320
binti Khuwailid radiallahu anha

00:38:20.320 --> 00:38:22.320
was Ummu Ayman. She was working

00:38:22.320 --> 00:38:24.320
with Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam, a woman

00:38:24.320 --> 00:38:26.320
from Africa who was a slave, who

00:38:26.320 --> 00:38:28.320
was freed. Listen very carefully,

00:38:28.320 --> 00:38:30.320
brings tears to the eyes. She accepted

00:38:30.320 --> 00:38:32.320
the message of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:38:32.320 --> 00:38:34.320
you are definitely a prophet

00:38:34.320 --> 00:38:36.320
of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam. I've

00:38:36.320 --> 00:38:38.320
watched you from the moment you were born

00:38:38.320 --> 00:38:40.320
and I know what's going on. And she

00:38:40.320 --> 00:38:42.320
outlived Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:38:42.320 --> 00:38:44.320
Later on in the life of

00:38:44.320 --> 00:38:46.320
Ummu Ayman radiallahu

00:38:46.320 --> 00:38:48.320
anha, the prophet sallallahu alayhi

00:38:48.320 --> 00:38:50.320
wasallam decided to make an announcement.

00:38:50.320 --> 00:38:52.320
What did he say? Whoever

00:38:52.320 --> 00:38:54.320
wants to marry a woman from

00:38:54.320 --> 00:38:56.320
Jannah, they should marry

00:38:56.320 --> 00:38:58.320
Ummu Ayman. Imagine.

00:38:58.320 --> 00:39:00.320
Whoever wants to marry a woman

00:39:00.320 --> 00:39:02.320
from Jannah should marry Ummu Ayman.

00:39:02.320 --> 00:39:04.320
This woman who was married

00:39:04.320 --> 00:39:06.320
before, she was the mother of

00:39:06.320 --> 00:39:08.320
Ayman. She had had a child before

00:39:08.320 --> 00:39:10.320
previously. On top of that she was

00:39:10.320 --> 00:39:12.320
a slave. On top of that she was from

00:39:12.320 --> 00:39:14.320
Africa. On top of that she looked after

00:39:14.320 --> 00:39:16.320
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam, he freed her.

00:39:16.320 --> 00:39:18.320
And now he is saying whoever

00:39:18.320 --> 00:39:20.320
wants to marry a woman from Jannah

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:22.320
should marry Ummu Ayman.

00:39:22.320 --> 00:39:24.320
And who got up and married her?

00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:26.320
None other than

00:39:26.320 --> 00:39:28.320
and the most beloved to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:39:28.320 --> 00:39:30.320
Zayd ibn Haritha.

00:39:30.320 --> 00:39:32.320
He was much younger than her.

00:39:32.320 --> 00:39:34.320
Much younger than her. He married

00:39:34.320 --> 00:39:36.320
her. And who did she give

00:39:36.320 --> 00:39:38.320
birth to? She is the mother of

00:39:38.320 --> 00:39:40.320
Usama bin Zayd radiallahu anha.

00:39:40.320 --> 00:39:42.320
One of the youngest leaders of the

00:39:42.320 --> 00:39:44.320
Muslim armies. She is the mother

00:39:44.320 --> 00:39:46.320
Ummu Ayman. And where did she pass

00:39:46.320 --> 00:39:48.320
away? She passed away later on

00:39:48.320 --> 00:39:50.320
in Madina Munawwara and is

00:39:50.320 --> 00:39:52.320
buried in Baqi' radiallahu anha

00:39:52.320 --> 00:39:54.320
wa'anis sahabiyati

00:39:54.320 --> 00:39:56.320
wa'anis sahabiyati ajma.

00:39:56.320 --> 00:39:58.320
May Allah be pleased with all the sahaba radiallahu

00:39:58.320 --> 00:40:00.320
anhum. They sacrificed their lives.

00:40:00.320 --> 00:40:02.320
And look at these people. It is

00:40:02.320 --> 00:40:04.320
reported that Zayd ibn

00:40:04.320 --> 00:40:06.320
Haritha was very very white in

00:40:06.320 --> 00:40:08.320
complexion. And Usama bin Zayd was

00:40:08.320 --> 00:40:10.320
very dark in complexion. So much so

00:40:10.320 --> 00:40:12.320
that people used to accuse

00:40:12.320 --> 00:40:14.320
the child of being not from this particular

00:40:14.320 --> 00:40:16.320
father until one day they

00:40:16.320 --> 00:40:18.320
were sleeping in the masjid. And

00:40:18.320 --> 00:40:20.320
the two feet were sticking out of the other side of

00:40:20.320 --> 00:40:22.320
the cover, the sheet. And one mudlaji

00:40:22.320 --> 00:40:24.320
a person who was an expert in lineage

00:40:24.320 --> 00:40:26.320
he came and as he's walking past

00:40:26.320 --> 00:40:28.320
he didn't know the story. He looked at

00:40:28.320 --> 00:40:30.320
the feet and he says

00:40:30.320 --> 00:40:32.320
These feet, some of them

00:40:32.320 --> 00:40:34.320
belong to the other. They are part of

00:40:34.320 --> 00:40:36.320
one and the same. So everyone

00:40:36.320 --> 00:40:38.320
was relieved to say Subhanallah.

00:40:38.320 --> 00:40:40.320
People used to say things. So the

00:40:40.320 --> 00:40:42.320
complex sometimes it comes from the lineage

00:40:42.320 --> 00:40:44.320
from the family. His mother was from

00:40:44.320 --> 00:40:46.320
Africa. Allahu Akbar. May

00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:48.320
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us.

00:40:48.320 --> 00:40:50.320
May we be from amongst those who

00:40:50.320 --> 00:40:52.320
understand and realize, look

00:40:52.320 --> 00:40:54.320
at where we are today. Sometimes

00:40:54.320 --> 00:40:56.320
we go backwards and yet Muhammad

00:40:56.320 --> 00:40:58.320
sallallahu alayhi wa sallam making

00:40:58.320 --> 00:41:00.320
a beautiful announcement.

00:41:00.320 --> 00:41:02.320
And this was Ummu Ayman.

00:41:02.320 --> 00:41:04.320
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless her.

00:41:04.320 --> 00:41:06.320
Now Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:41:06.320 --> 00:41:08.320
when he was young, he took

00:41:08.320 --> 00:41:10.320
part in several

00:41:10.320 --> 00:41:12.320
incidents, several great matters

00:41:12.320 --> 00:41:14.320
that occurred. One of them was known as

00:41:14.320 --> 00:41:16.320
Hilful Fudul. The

00:41:16.320 --> 00:41:18.320
pledge that was

00:41:18.320 --> 00:41:20.320
pledged in one of the houses in Makkah

00:41:20.320 --> 00:41:22.320
al-Mukarramah. Let me give you a quick synopsis

00:41:22.320 --> 00:41:24.320
of what happened. There was a

00:41:24.320 --> 00:41:26.320
man from Yemen who had come up to Makkah

00:41:26.320 --> 00:41:28.320
and he was known as Zabidi

00:41:28.320 --> 00:41:30.320
because he was from those people of Zabid.

00:41:30.320 --> 00:41:32.320
So this Zabidi man,

00:41:32.320 --> 00:41:34.320
he had come with a bit of

00:41:34.320 --> 00:41:36.320
merchandise and so on and he was dealing

00:41:36.320 --> 00:41:38.320
with a man known as Al-Aas ibn Wa'il,

00:41:38.320 --> 00:41:40.320
the father of Amr ibn Al-Aas.

00:41:40.320 --> 00:41:42.320
Al-Aas ibn Wa'il died as a non-Muslim

00:41:42.320 --> 00:41:44.320
but Amr ibn Al-Aas was a great Sahabi

00:41:44.320 --> 00:41:46.320
and we know he was one of those who conquered Egypt.

00:41:46.320 --> 00:41:48.320
And this

00:41:48.320 --> 00:41:50.320
Al-Aas ibn Wa'il cheated

00:41:50.320 --> 00:41:52.320
this Zabidi out of his wealth

00:41:52.320 --> 00:41:54.320
because this Zabidi wanted to go

00:41:54.320 --> 00:41:56.320
out to the Kaaba and do his

00:41:56.320 --> 00:41:58.320
tawaf and what have you with the idols

00:41:58.320 --> 00:42:00.320
and whatever it was. So he left this wealth

00:42:00.320 --> 00:42:02.320
with Al-Aas ibn Wa'il.

00:42:02.320 --> 00:42:04.320
And when he came

00:42:04.320 --> 00:42:06.320
back, the man says, there's nothing for you here.

00:42:06.320 --> 00:42:08.320
What do you mean? I gave you all my wealth?

00:42:08.320 --> 00:42:10.320
You're telling me there's nothing for me here?

00:42:10.320 --> 00:42:12.320
So he started calling out.

00:42:12.320 --> 00:42:14.320
Now Al-Aas ibn Wa'il was one of the seniors

00:42:14.320 --> 00:42:16.320
in Quraysh.

00:42:16.320 --> 00:42:18.320
No one dared take his name.

00:42:18.320 --> 00:42:20.320
And if this man had gone to

00:42:20.320 --> 00:42:22.320
people to tell them anything, they wouldn't believe.

00:42:22.320 --> 00:42:24.320
Anyway, he did go to a few people

00:42:24.320 --> 00:42:26.320
and say, Al-Aas ibn Wa'il has stolen

00:42:26.320 --> 00:42:28.320
my wealth. And they said, what are you

00:42:28.320 --> 00:42:30.320
talking about? That can never be. This is one of

00:42:30.320 --> 00:42:32.320
the noblemen here. So

00:42:32.320 --> 00:42:34.320
he says, no, he has stolen

00:42:34.320 --> 00:42:36.320
my wealth. And he went, nobody

00:42:36.320 --> 00:42:38.320
helped him and in fact he was

00:42:38.320 --> 00:42:40.320
oppressed because his wealth was usurped

00:42:40.320 --> 00:42:42.320
by the people of Quraysh. There was one way

00:42:42.320 --> 00:42:44.320
he was going to achieve assistance.

00:42:44.320 --> 00:42:46.320
He had eloquence of the tongue. This is Zabidi.

00:42:46.320 --> 00:42:48.320
He got up, Jabal Abi Qubais.

00:42:48.320 --> 00:42:50.320
He got up one of the mounds there

00:42:50.320 --> 00:42:52.320
near Kaaba and he started

00:42:52.320 --> 00:42:54.320
singing his poems.

00:42:54.320 --> 00:42:56.320
What were the poems? The poems

00:42:56.320 --> 00:42:58.320
were making mention of how Quraysh

00:42:58.320 --> 00:43:00.320
stole his wealth.

00:43:00.320 --> 00:43:02.320
And how Al-Aas ibn Wa'il has

00:43:02.320 --> 00:43:04.320
stolen his wealth and they are thugs and

00:43:04.320 --> 00:43:06.320
robbers and they're all in kahoot and so

00:43:06.320 --> 00:43:08.320
on. And he started singing some poems

00:43:08.320 --> 00:43:10.320
and you know, I told you yesterday,

00:43:10.320 --> 00:43:12.320
they were crazy about poetry.

00:43:12.320 --> 00:43:14.320
A man's status would raise

00:43:14.320 --> 00:43:16.320
because of poetry. And a man

00:43:16.320 --> 00:43:18.320
would be considered a

00:43:18.320 --> 00:43:20.320
leader and a chief because he came with something

00:43:20.320 --> 00:43:22.320
powerful. This man came with

00:43:22.320 --> 00:43:24.320
powerful words that lasted up to today.

00:43:24.320 --> 00:43:26.320
For your information, they were all

00:43:26.320 --> 00:43:28.320
negative about Quraysh and about

00:43:28.320 --> 00:43:30.320
what had happened. So they wanted to do

