to do business on her

00:53:38.320 --> 00:53:40.320
behalf. She was a woman. She

00:53:40.320 --> 00:53:42.320
would stay in Makkah. But he could go

00:53:42.320 --> 00:53:44.320
up to a Sham and come

00:53:44.320 --> 00:53:46.320
down. That was Allah's planning. Why?

00:53:46.320 --> 00:53:48.320
When you're going up to Sham

00:53:48.320 --> 00:53:50.320
in the Syrian region, you pass

00:53:50.320 --> 00:53:52.320
Madinah Munawwarah. And the Prophet SAW

00:53:52.320 --> 00:53:54.320
became acquainted with Madinah

00:53:54.320 --> 00:53:56.320
and its people from a very early age.

00:53:56.320 --> 00:53:58.320
Did we ever know that? And he already

00:53:58.320 --> 00:54:00.320
passed there and he would go, stop

00:54:00.320 --> 00:54:02.320
over, continue, go up and so on.

00:54:02.320 --> 00:54:04.320
Literally today, we call it

00:54:04.320 --> 00:54:06.320
a container business. Nowadays

00:54:06.320 --> 00:54:08.320
we have a ship coming from MashaAllah

00:54:08.320 --> 00:54:10.320
China and Hong Kong and Taiwan. It's a ship.

00:54:10.320 --> 00:54:12.320
It comes and it docks in Durban and then we

00:54:12.320 --> 00:54:14.320
busy following it by phone. And we've got

00:54:14.320 --> 00:54:16.320
this agent and that agent. This, at

00:54:16.320 --> 00:54:18.320
that particular time, this was equivalent

00:54:18.320 --> 00:54:20.320
to the containers that people of this

00:54:20.320 --> 00:54:22.320
part of the world are acquainted to

00:54:22.320 --> 00:54:24.320
or acquainted with. So

00:54:24.320 --> 00:54:26.320
Muhammad SAW used to go

00:54:26.320 --> 00:54:28.320
with the caravans. And

00:54:28.320 --> 00:54:30.320
Khadija RA, at that

00:54:30.320 --> 00:54:32.320
time, she sent her slave

00:54:32.320 --> 00:54:34.320
known as Maysara

00:54:34.320 --> 00:54:36.320
with Muhammad SAW.

00:54:36.320 --> 00:54:38.320
And she said, you go with him.

00:54:38.320 --> 00:54:40.320
And he noticed this man respected

00:54:40.320 --> 00:54:42.320
him. Imagine a slave. People, today

00:54:42.320 --> 00:54:44.320
we treat our, those who

00:54:44.320 --> 00:54:46.320
work for us are not even slaves. They are

00:54:46.320 --> 00:54:48.320
free like me and you. And

00:54:48.320 --> 00:54:50.320
we treat them so badly. We swear,

00:54:50.320 --> 00:54:52.320
we shout, we overburden them

00:54:52.320 --> 00:54:54.320
and we tell them so much and we still call

00:54:54.320 --> 00:54:56.320
ourselves followers of Muhammad SAW.

00:54:56.320 --> 00:54:58.320
What a shame. We are insulting

00:54:58.320 --> 00:55:00.320
our religion. People, you know

00:55:00.320 --> 00:55:02.320
when they go back to their villages

00:55:02.320 --> 00:55:04.320
after, when the holidays are there,

00:55:04.320 --> 00:55:06.320
they sit and they discuss, oh I work in Nirvana.

00:55:06.320 --> 00:55:08.320
Where's that? Oh it's in Polokwani.

00:55:08.320 --> 00:55:10.320
You know I work for these Muslims.

00:55:10.320 --> 00:55:12.320
They can swear. They shout. You know

00:55:12.320 --> 00:55:14.320
the uncle wanted to beat me also.

00:55:14.320 --> 00:55:16.320
And all of them get a bad picture of

00:55:16.320 --> 00:55:18.320
Islam. Do we know that? And the same

00:55:18.320 --> 00:55:20.320
people when they sit around a fire in the village

00:55:20.320 --> 00:55:22.320
at the month end or at the end of the year

00:55:22.320 --> 00:55:24.320
and they say, you know what? We have

00:55:24.320 --> 00:55:26.320
Muslims. They look after us. They respect

00:55:26.320 --> 00:55:28.320
us. They don't give us food that

00:55:28.320 --> 00:55:30.320
is fit for the bin. But they give us a portion

00:55:30.320 --> 00:55:32.320
of what they've cooked. Allah

00:55:32.320 --> 00:55:34.320
Akbar.

00:55:34.320 --> 00:55:36.320
Allah Akbar. Wallahi I'm not lying to you.

00:55:36.320 --> 00:55:38.320
These are facts. Muhammad SAW

00:55:38.320 --> 00:55:40.320
treated Maysara who was a slave

00:55:40.320 --> 00:55:42.320
with utmost respect, dignity.

00:55:42.320 --> 00:55:44.320
A man afforded the

00:55:44.320 --> 00:55:46.320
credentials. Subhanallah. He was

00:55:46.320 --> 00:55:48.320
given whatever a man deserves.

00:55:48.320 --> 00:55:50.320
And at the same time, honesty.

00:55:50.320 --> 00:55:52.320
No usurping. Imagine you've got millions

00:55:52.320 --> 00:55:54.320
of rands. You and someone else say, you know

00:55:54.320 --> 00:55:56.320
what? Just don't say anything. You take some, I take

00:55:56.320 --> 00:55:58.320
some. That doesn't happen inshallah amongst

00:55:58.320 --> 00:56:00.320
Muslimin. But there's a lot of people who do

00:56:00.320 --> 00:56:02.320
do that. May Allah SWT

00:56:02.320 --> 00:56:04.320
safeguard us. Muhammad SAW did not

00:56:04.320 --> 00:56:06.320
do that. Honesty. Every cent.

00:56:06.320 --> 00:56:08.320
Every little coin was

00:56:08.320 --> 00:56:10.320
accounted for. And so much

00:56:10.320 --> 00:56:12.320
blessing in business. When the

00:56:12.320 --> 00:56:14.320
caravan used to come back with Muhammad SAW

00:56:14.320 --> 00:56:16.320
The Prophet was

00:56:16.320 --> 00:56:18.320
so much. There was so much blessing.

00:56:18.320 --> 00:56:20.320
Khadija binti Khuwailid radiallahu anha.

00:56:20.320 --> 00:56:22.320
She had a friend.

00:56:22.320 --> 00:56:24.320
Her friend was known as Nafisa binti

00:56:24.320 --> 00:56:26.320
Munabbi. And she tells her friend,

00:56:26.320 --> 00:56:28.320
hey, you know what? This guy here

00:56:28.320 --> 00:56:30.320
is worth getting married to. Man. What a man.

00:56:30.320 --> 00:56:32.320
Look at him. Honest.

00:56:32.320 --> 00:56:34.320
The slave has come back to me. And he says

00:56:34.320 --> 00:56:36.320
this man is of high

00:56:36.320 --> 00:56:38.320
morals and standards. The highest I've ever seen.

00:56:38.320 --> 00:56:40.320
And the man is full of respect

00:56:40.320 --> 00:56:42.320
and dignity. Everyone. Honest.

00:56:42.320 --> 00:56:44.320
He doesn't even usurp

00:56:44.320 --> 00:56:46.320
a single fraction of the wealth.

00:56:46.320 --> 00:56:48.320
So she

00:56:48.320 --> 00:56:50.320
went to him one time. You see

00:56:50.320 --> 00:56:52.320
the women sometimes they have guts. You see?

00:56:52.320 --> 00:56:54.320
So she went to him and she suggested

00:56:54.320 --> 00:56:56.320
hey, what's happening here? You see?

00:56:56.320 --> 00:56:58.320
Now look at this woman. Older

00:56:58.320 --> 00:57:00.320
than him by quite a bit. Married

00:57:00.320 --> 00:57:02.320
twice. And both of the husbands

00:57:02.320 --> 00:57:04.320
passed away. One after the other.

00:57:04.320 --> 00:57:06.320
You know in our community there's a widow.

00:57:06.320 --> 00:57:08.320
Only Allah knows how we look at her.

00:57:08.320 --> 00:57:10.320
Yet the hadith speaks about the lofty rank

00:57:10.320 --> 00:57:12.320
of those who support widows and orphans.

00:57:12.320 --> 00:57:14.320
A sa'i. The one who

00:57:14.320 --> 00:57:16.320
supports widows and orphans is

00:57:16.320 --> 00:57:18.320
equivalent to the one who stands

00:57:18.320 --> 00:57:20.320
in salah all night, every night.

00:57:20.320 --> 00:57:22.320
And the one who fasts all day, every day.

00:57:22.320 --> 00:57:24.320
That's the reward.

00:57:24.320 --> 00:57:26.320
So this widow

00:57:26.320 --> 00:57:28.320
she sends, or this friend

00:57:28.320 --> 00:57:30.320
went to say this. And he

00:57:30.320 --> 00:57:32.320
after a while, whatever he may have done

00:57:32.320 --> 00:57:34.320
he felt a little bit positive about it.

00:57:34.320 --> 00:57:36.320
And he spoke to his

00:57:36.320 --> 00:57:38.320
uncle. It is reported

00:57:38.320 --> 00:57:40.320
that he spoke to Abu Talib. It is also

00:57:40.320 --> 00:57:42.320
reported that he spoke to Hamza.

00:57:42.320 --> 00:57:44.320
And Hamza went with him

00:57:44.320 --> 00:57:46.320
to Khadija.

00:57:46.320 --> 00:57:48.320
And her family.

00:57:48.320 --> 00:57:50.320
And they

00:57:50.320 --> 00:57:52.320
made a proposal in what we would

00:57:52.320 --> 00:57:54.320
call, they became engaged

00:57:54.320 --> 00:57:56.320
so to speak. They agreed that we

00:57:56.320 --> 00:57:58.320
would get married. And the marriage was

00:57:58.320 --> 00:58:00.320
then attended by

00:58:00.320 --> 00:58:02.320
Abu Talib himself. And a

00:58:02.320 --> 00:58:04.320
few others. And in such a little

00:58:04.320 --> 00:58:06.320
while they were married. For your information today

00:58:06.320 --> 00:58:08.320
we have engagements. In Islam

00:58:08.320 --> 00:58:10.320
there is nothing like these engagements.

00:58:10.320 --> 00:58:12.320
If you look at it, what is

00:58:12.320 --> 00:58:14.320
an engagement in Islam? It is

00:58:14.320 --> 00:58:16.320
just the mere confirmation

00:58:16.320 --> 00:58:18.320
that these two will be getting

00:58:18.320 --> 00:58:20.320
married. That's all.

00:58:20.320 --> 00:58:22.320
Nothing else. Today we have a big function

00:58:22.320 --> 00:58:24.320
bigger than the waleema is an engagement.

00:58:24.320 --> 00:58:26.320
And after that what happens?

00:58:26.320 --> 00:58:28.320
It was broken.

00:58:28.320 --> 00:58:30.320
You see that guy was a rascal. We didn't

00:58:30.320 --> 00:58:32.320
know. We found out later. Why?

00:58:32.320 --> 00:58:34.320
Because you did it the wrong way.

00:58:34.320 --> 00:58:36.320
You don't need a big engagement. Get the

00:58:36.320 --> 00:58:38.320
nikah done as simple and straight forward

00:58:38.320 --> 00:58:40.320
and inshallah let them start living

00:58:40.320 --> 00:58:42.320
together. An engagement the way

00:58:42.320 --> 00:58:44.320
we do it today where a year later we

00:58:44.320 --> 00:58:46.320
have a nikah. That one year we only

00:58:46.320 --> 00:58:48.320
allow them to engage in sin. That's all that

00:58:48.320 --> 00:58:50.320
happened. Nothing else. Nothing positive

00:58:50.320 --> 00:58:52.320
can come out of a prolonged

00:58:52.320 --> 00:58:54.320
engagement. I see some of the youngsters

00:58:54.320 --> 00:58:56.320
are smiling. Perhaps this is a good point

00:58:56.320 --> 00:58:58.320
for their fathers. May Allah SWT

00:58:58.320 --> 00:59:00.320
make it easy for us as parents.

00:59:00.320 --> 00:59:02.320
You don't need to wait. Allah has provided for you

00:59:02.320 --> 00:59:04.320
and Allah has given you. Make it easy

00:59:04.320 --> 00:59:06.320
for them. So Rasulullah SAW

00:59:06.320 --> 00:59:08.320
thereafter

00:59:08.320 --> 00:59:10.320
got married to Khadija Binti Khuwailid

00:59:10.320 --> 00:59:12.320
RA. And

00:59:12.320 --> 00:59:14.320
she was much older.

00:59:14.320 --> 00:59:16.320
The narrations

00:59:16.320 --> 00:59:18.320
that are

00:59:18.320 --> 00:59:20.320
most common make mention of his

00:59:20.320 --> 00:59:22.320
age and her age. His age was

00:59:22.320 --> 00:59:24.320
25 years old when he got married

00:59:24.320 --> 00:59:26.320
according to everyone. And her

00:59:26.320 --> 00:59:28.320
age was 40 years

00:59:28.320 --> 00:59:30.320
according to the majority. Some say

00:59:30.320 --> 00:59:32.320
that she was 28 years old.

00:59:32.320 --> 00:59:34.320
This is obviously just a narration. I'm making mention

00:59:34.320 --> 00:59:36.320
of it for you to know that there is

00:59:36.320 --> 00:59:38.320
a narration of that. But we

00:59:38.320 --> 00:59:40.320
all know that the vast

00:59:40.320 --> 00:59:42.320
majority say she was 40 years old.

00:59:42.320 --> 00:59:44.320
She was already divorced. Sorry. She was

00:59:44.320 --> 00:59:46.320
already widowed twice

00:59:46.320 --> 00:59:48.320
and this was her third husband.

00:59:48.320 --> 00:59:50.320
And this was his first wife.

00:59:50.320 --> 00:59:52.320
And he married her and

00:59:52.320 --> 00:59:54.320
he did not marry any other woman

00:59:54.320 --> 00:59:56.320
whilst she was alive.

00:59:56.320 --> 00:59:58.320
RA. And for your

00:59:58.320 --> 01:00:00.320
information, those who say he was a

01:00:00.320 --> 01:00:02.320
pedophile, I seek refuge with Allah. Those who say

01:00:02.320 --> 01:00:04.320
he was full of lust and desires,

01:00:04.320 --> 01:00:06.320
not at all. If that was

01:00:06.320 --> 01:00:08.320
the case, at this young age of 25,

01:00:08.320 --> 01:00:10.320
he would have chosen the best

01:00:10.320 --> 01:00:12.320
of girls of the whole of Quraish.

01:00:12.320 --> 01:00:14.320
As it is, he had a very lofty

01:00:14.320 --> 01:00:16.320
name in Quraish. But

01:00:16.320 --> 01:00:18.320
he decided to go for someone who was mature.

01:00:18.320 --> 01:00:20.320
And it was Allah's plan because

01:00:20.320 --> 01:00:22.320
for your information, Allah had

01:00:22.320 --> 01:00:24.320
already made Khadija

01:00:24.320 --> 01:00:26.320
Binti Khuwailid with qualities that were

01:00:26.320 --> 01:00:28.320
needed in order to

01:00:28.320 --> 01:00:30.320
comfort Muhammad SAW

01:00:30.320 --> 01:00:32.320
the day revelation came.

01:00:32.320 --> 01:00:34.320
So this was all the plan of Allah

01:00:34.320 --> 01:00:36.320
SAW. So

01:00:36.320 --> 01:00:38.320
Rasulullah SAW married

01:00:38.320 --> 01:00:40.320
her and she is the one who

01:00:40.320 --> 01:00:42.320
bore his children

01:00:42.320 --> 01:00:44.320
and he had six children

01:00:44.320 --> 01:00:46.320
from Khadija Binti Khuwailid RA.

01:00:46.320 --> 01:00:48.320
Two boys. They both passed

01:00:48.320 --> 01:00:50.320
away. One died in childhood.

01:00:50.320 --> 01:00:52.320
His name was Al-Qasim.

01:00:52.320 --> 01:00:54.320
Childhood meaning not infancy.

01:00:54.320 --> 01:00:56.320
But they say he could jump onto

01:00:56.320 --> 01:00:58.320
an animal. He could jump

01:00:58.320 --> 01:01:00.320
onto the horse or the camel.

01:01:00.320 --> 01:01:02.320
And at that age, he passed away.

01:01:02.320 --> 01:01:04.320
Al-Qasim.

01:01:04.320 --> 01:01:06.320
And this is why he is also known as

01:01:06.320 --> 01:01:08.320
Abu Al-Qasim SAW.

01:01:08.320 --> 01:01:10.320
And the other one,

01:01:10.320 --> 01:01:12.320
his name was Abdullah. He passed away

01:01:12.320 --> 01:01:14.320
in infancy. Imagine

01:01:14.320 --> 01:01:16.320
those who've lost children, even Muhammad SAW

01:01:16.320 --> 01:01:18.320
has lost children. And here

01:01:18.320 --> 01:01:20.320
you have both of his boys

01:01:20.320 --> 01:01:22.320
lost. Later

01:01:22.320 --> 01:01:24.320
on, there was another boy by Mario Al-Qibtiya.

01:01:24.320 --> 01:01:26.320
We will get to that inshallah. Ibrahim.

01:01:26.320 --> 01:01:28.320
He was also lost.

01:01:28.320 --> 01:01:30.320
But this was all prior to prophethood.

01:01:30.320 --> 01:01:32.320
And he had four girls.

01:01:32.320 --> 01:01:34.320
Zainab, Ruqayya,

01:01:34.320 --> 01:01:36.320
Umm Kulthum

01:01:36.320 --> 01:01:38.320
and Fatima.

01:01:38.320 --> 01:01:40.320
May Allah be pleased with all of them.

01:01:40.320 --> 01:01:42.320
They lived. When he came with

01:01:42.320 --> 01:01:44.320
prophethood, they accepted Islam.

01:01:44.320 --> 01:01:46.320
When they all

01:01:46.320 --> 01:01:48.320
made Hijra as well. May Allah

01:01:48.320 --> 01:01:50.320
SAW bless us all.

01:01:50.320 --> 01:01:52.320
May Allah SAW grant us

01:01:52.320 --> 01:01:54.320
goodness from the Seerah. This

01:01:54.320 --> 01:01:56.320
is only a tip of the iceberg

01:01:56.320 --> 01:01:58.320
inshallah. We hope that Allah

01:01:58.320 --> 01:02:00.320
SAW increases the love

01:02:00.320 --> 01:02:02.320
we have in our hearts for Muhammad SAW

01:02:02.320 --> 01:02:04.320
in a way that

01:02:04.320 --> 01:02:06.320
it can be seen on our physical

01:02:06.320 --> 01:02:08.320
features and faces. And in a way

01:02:08.320 --> 01:02:10.320
that inshallah will result ultimately

01:02:10.320 --> 01:02:12.320
in us earning Jannah through

01:02:12.320 --> 01:02:14.320
obeying the instructions that

01:02:14.320 --> 01:02:16.320
were from Allah SAW that came to

01:02:16.320 --> 01:02:18.320
us through Muhammad SAW.

01:02:18.320 --> 01:02:20.320
Until we meet again tomorrow to continue

01:02:20.320 --> 01:02:22.320
this episode, we say,

01:02:22.320 --> 01:02:24.320
wa salallahu wa sallam wa baraka ala nabina Muhammad

01:02:24.320 --> 01:02:26.320
subhanallah wa bihamdihi, subhanaka

01:02:26.320 --> 01:02:28.320
allahum wa bihamdik, nashhadu alla ilaha illa anta

01:02:28.320 --> 01:02:30.320
nastaghfiruka wa natubu inayki
